"Why distill at all"},"20":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-5","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance","content":"One gate for everything entering the graph: a claim arrives via MCP `ingest` or intake distillation, is embedded, then merged into something already known or routed down the kern tree. Two stages, failing differently:"},"21":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-6","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance","content":"**Distillation** — transcript → claims. The only LLM call on the path; decides *whether* anything is kept."},"22":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-7","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance","content":"**Acceptance** — places a claim. Pure vector math + traversal, no model; decides *where* it lives or whether it collapses into an existing thought."},"23":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-8","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"One LLM pass over the whole delta → JSON array of `{text, kind, valid_from?}`. Forgiving parse — prose around the array, double-nesting, blank entries tolerated or dropped. Outage safety lives in the return value:"},"24":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-9","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Result"},"25":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-10","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Action"},"26":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-11","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Claims"},"27":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-12","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Process; archive the delta only after every claim committed."},"28":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-13","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Empty array"},"29":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-14","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Model judged nothing worth keeping; archive."},"30":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-15","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Nothing usable (dead endpoint, timeout, no parseable JSON)"},"31":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-16","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"Leave queued, retry. Nothing silently lost."},"32":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-17","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#distillation","content":"A reason model that persistently answers in prose looks like a permanent outage: deltas never lost, never archived, intake retries forever. `.kern/intake/` growing while the graph does not → suspect the model's instruction following."},"33":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-18","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"Seven built-in; the `claim_kind` tool registers more:"},"34":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-19","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"Kind"},"35":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-20","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"What it holds"},"36":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-21","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`preference`"},"37":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-22","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"How the user wants things done."},"38":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-23","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`decision`"},"39":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-24","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"A choice made, with rationale."},"40":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-25","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`project`"},"41":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-26","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"Ongoing state of the work."},"42":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-27","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`fact`"},"43":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-28","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"A durable truth about the domain."},"44":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-29","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`code-fact`"},"45":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-30","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"A structural truth about the codebase."},"46":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-31","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`reference`"},"47":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-32","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"An external pointer worth keeping."},"48":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-33","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`procedural`"},"49":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-34","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"A learned workflow or convention."},"50":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-35","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"Invented kind falls back to `fact` — type precision lost, never the claim."},"51":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-36","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"`valid_from` kept only when it parses as a real ISO timestamp."},"52":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-37","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#claim-kinds","content":"Distilled claims enter at confidence 0.6 — a model's reading, not your assertion."},"53":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-38","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#routing","content":"Descends the kern tree by graviton (focus vector + mass). Every child scored `cosine_distance / mass`, converted to an acceptance probability against the kern's radii; best probability below the floor (0.5) = no match. Mass is the tuning knob — heavier attracts from further away."},"54":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-39","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#routing","content":"Root is a pure dispatcher; no match at the root falls into `generic` — dense `generic` clusters later promote into new gravitons."},"55":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-40","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#routing","content":"A named kern can refuse — a poor fit lands in a reusable unnamed holding-pen child, descent continues."},"56":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-41","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#routing","content":"Descent bounded at 64 levels."},"57":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-42","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#routing","content":"Commit: index the vector, `Similarity` edge to nearest neighbour, `Provenance` edge to source document, supersede path if the claim carries an external id."},"58":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-43","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#merge-not-reject","content":"Near-duplicate (cosine ≥ dedup threshold — 0.98 on default `relaxed`) is *evidence*: reinforces the existing thought's confidence."},"59":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-44","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#merge-not-reject","content":"Text/vector never overwritten (id = content hash). Different phrasing → `Rephrase` edge; only a *same-kind* rephrase reaches the contradiction detector — a claim must never supersede a fact."},"60":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-45","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#merge-not-reject","content":"Genuine rejection is narrow: empty text, an unembeddable chunk. Embedding failures retried with backoff; job outcomes distinguish partial from clean success."},"61":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-46","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#why-distill-at-all","content":"Raw-transcript embedding: conversational noise in the vector space, no type (no kind-aware routing, same-kind supersede guard, or kind-filtered queries), no consolidation — five phrasings become five permanent neighbours."},"62":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-47","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#why-distill-at-all","content":"Cost: seconds of latency (async, never blocks a session), hard dependency on a reason endpoint, non-deterministic output. Buys: everything after distillation is deterministic — one non-deterministic step at write time, none at read time."},"63":{"id":"/concepts/acceptance-48","page_id":"/concepts/acceptance","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/acceptance#why-distill-at-all","content":"Next: Retrieval · Heat & compaction · Time & supersede · Intake & recall in a session"},"64":{"id":"/concepts/architecture","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"page","content":"Architecture","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture"},"65":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-0","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"One trade, every decision"},"66":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-1","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"The flow"},"67":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-2","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#whats-in-the-graph","content":"What's in the graph"},"68":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-3","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#nothing-is-deleted","content":"Nothing is deleted"},"69":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-4","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#thirteen-mcp-tools","content":"Thirteen MCP tools"},"70":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-5","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#fail-open-but-counted","content":"Fail-open, but counted"},"71":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-6","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/architecture#staying-current","content":"Staying current"},"72":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-7","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture","content":"One long-running **memory daemon** per working directory owns a knowledge graph in `.kern/`, keeps it small on its own, serves context at recall time. Nothing captured automatically — every write is a caller's call."},"73":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-8","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture","content":"> **Recall costs no LLM call.** The default query path is a sub-millisecond graph walk — no network hop, no model, no cloud. All expensive thinking happens before the query: LLM at write time, CPU in the background tick."},"74":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-9","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Decision"},"75":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-10","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Why"},"76":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-11","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"One daemon per cwd, always running"},"77":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-12","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"The background tick needs somewhere to live."},"78":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-13","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Distill at ingest, not at query"},"79":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-14","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"LLM cost paid once per session, not per lookup."},"80":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-15","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"A graph, not a vector bag"},"81":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-16","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Reason edges are precomputed *why*. Walking is free; deriving isn't."},"82":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-17","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"IDs are content hashes"},"83":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-18","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Identical text = same node everywhere. Merge is set union — no coordinator."},"84":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-19","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Heat + decay + GC"},"85":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-20","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Nobody prunes by hand, so the graph forgets on its own."},"86":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-21","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"All-internal, no pluggable backend"},"87":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-22","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"An external store adds a network hop to the one path that must stay sub-ms."},"88":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-23","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Fail open everywhere"},"89":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-24","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#one-trade-every-decision","content":"Memory that breaks a session is worse than memory that misses."},"90":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-25","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"Two caller-driven write entries — MCP `ingest`, or a transcript dropped into `.kern/intake/` — same graph. Four independent loops:"},"91":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-26","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"**Write** — claim embedded, deduped, placed."},"92":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-27","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"**Read** — seed candidates, expand over edges, rank, return."},"93":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-28","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"**Maintenance** — tick every 60s: deposit heat, cluster, re-embed, evict, persist. `tick.interval_secs = 0` disables."},"94":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-29","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#the-flow","content":"**Federation** (off by default) — gossip merges entity bodies with peers."},"95":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-30","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#whats-in-the-graph","content":"**Entities** (\"thoughts\", \"claims\") — a distilled fact, decision, or preference: typed, evidence-weighted confidence, heat, vector, bi-temporal validity window."},"96":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-31","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#whats-in-the-graph","content":"**Reasons** (edges) — a *justified* link: labeled relation with its own text and vector, not a similarity score."},"97":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-32","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#whats-in-the-graph","content":"Entities live in **kerns**, a tree of buckets. Root is a pure dispatcher; named children are **gravitons** — seeded focus attractors. Ingest routes to the nearest graviton scaled by mass; no match falls into `generic`; dense `generic` clusters promote into new gravitons. Details: The graph · Acceptance & routing."},"98":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-33","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#nothing-is-deleted","content":"Updated or contradicted claim is **superseded**, never removed — the old revision keeps its validity window; query `as_of` or `include_history`. The update-vs-contradiction call needs an LLM, so it runs in the tick, never on the read path. See Time & contradiction."},"99":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-34","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#thirteen-mcp-tools","content":"`query`, `ingest`, `link`, `forget` (Facts are immune), `degrade`, `move`, `health`, `graviton`, `claim_kind`, `pulse`, `gc`, `intake_drain`, `setup`. Transports: stdio default, HTTP/SSE opt-in. See MCP tools."},"100":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-35","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#fail-open-but-counted","content":"Every degradation returns something instead of erroring. Panicking tick tasks, dropped cold rows, embed-model mismatches, rejected query vectors, chunks lost to a dead embed endpoint — counted, reported by `health`; `kern health` prints `degraded:` only when a counter is nonzero. Counting is not fixing — it just says so."},"101":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-36","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#staying-current","content":"**Auto-restart on attach** — `kern mcp` compares the daemon's build + config fingerprint against its own; gracefully replaces a stale daemon."},"102":{"id":"/concepts/architecture-37","page_id":"/concepts/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/architecture#staying-current","content":"**Hot reload** (Unix, default on) — daemon watches its own binary; a new build drains, flushes, hands the socket to a successor without dropping connections."},"103":{"id":"/concepts/federation","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"page","content":"Federation","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation"},"104":{"id":"/concepts/federation-0","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-daemon-would-want-a-peer","content":"Why a daemon would want a peer"},"105":{"id":"/concepts/federation-1","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#discovery-and-gossip","content":"Discovery and gossip"},"106":{"id":"/concepts/federation-2","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"What crosses the wire"},"107":{"id":"/concepts/federation-3","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"Why a CRDT and not a leader"},"108":{"id":"/concepts/federation-4","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#contradicting-facts-on-two-machines","content":"Contradicting facts on two machines"},"109":{"id":"/concepts/federation-5","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#remote-data-is-quarantined","content":"Remote data is quarantined"},"110":{"id":"/concepts/federation-6","page_id":"/concepts/federation","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/federation#turning-it-on","content":"Turning it on"},"111":{"id":"/concepts/federation-7","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation","content":"Several kern daemons on one network share what they have learned — no coordinator, no primary replica. kern's least mature subsystem; the transport protects nothing."},"112":{"id":"/concepts/federation-8","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation","content":"**Off by default** — keep it off unless deliberately experimenting."},"113":{"id":"/concepts/federation-9","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation","content":"**Works today:** peer heartbeats, multicast discovery, scope announcements, entity-body sync into a quarantined remote namespace, CRDT counter and last-write-wins deltas, single-entity fetch."},"114":{"id":"/concepts/federation-10","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation","content":"**Wired but dead:** OR-Set deltas for statement text — content-addressed ids make imported text a forgery; the sender emits empty, the receiver rejects."},"115":{"id":"/concepts/federation-11","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation","content":"**Not built:** authentication, encryption, anti-entropy, any guarantee a cold entity eventually reaches every peer."},"116":{"id":"/concepts/federation-12","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-daemon-would-want-a-peer","content":"One daemon per working directory is the right boundary except for **two machines doing the same work** — the incident debugged on the laptop at 11pm that the workstation daemon never saw. Federation: a fact learned once, available everywhere you work. Not scale, not sharding."},"117":{"id":"/concepts/federation-13","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-daemon-would-want-a-peer","content":"Daemons are laptops — they sleep, miss messages, rejoin elsewhere. Leaderless design; the merge tolerates offline peers, out-of-order delivery, duplicates."},"118":{"id":"/concepts/federation-14","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#discovery-and-gossip","content":"**Discovery** — plaintext `kern:<network_id>:<tcp_addr>` broadcast to a UDP multicast group every 10 seconds. Adopted only on matching `network_id` — how unrelated fleets on one LAN stay apart; set a shared `network_id` to pair daemons."},"119":{"id":"/concepts/federation-15","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#discovery-and-gossip","content":"Multicast is routinely dropped by wireless APs, container bridges, VPNs — the reliable path is an explicit `peers` list. An opt-in public seed exists and defaults off."},"120":{"id":"/concepts/federation-16","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#discovery-and-gossip","content":"**Gossip** — push flooding with dedup, fanout 3 random peers. Delivery is *probabilistic* — nothing guarantees a message reaches a given peer."},"121":{"id":"/concepts/federation-17","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Message"},"122":{"id":"/concepts/federation-18","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Content"},"123":{"id":"/concepts/federation-19","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"PeerExchange"},"124":{"id":"/concepts/federation-20","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"30s heartbeat; unknown addresses adopted up to a 50-peer ceiling."},"125":{"id":"/concepts/federation-21","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Sphere"},"126":{"id":"/concepts/federation-22","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"A node's root scope; stored by receivers as a read-only *phantom kern*."},"127":{"id":"/concepts/federation-23","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"EntitySync"},"128":{"id":"/concepts/federation-24","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Each heartbeat: the 32 hottest local entities."},"129":{"id":"/concepts/federation-25","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Delta"},"130":{"id":"/concepts/federation-26","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Incremental CRDT updates: access/traversal counts, reason scores, validity windows."},"131":{"id":"/concepts/federation-27","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Pulse / Question / Fetch"},"132":{"id":"/concepts/federation-28","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Activation spreading, cross-network questions, the single-entity fetch backing them."},"133":{"id":"/concepts/federation-29","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#what-crosses-the-wire","content":"Only the hottest entities are broadcast; a fact captured once and never recalled may never be selected, and there is no anti-entropy or catch-up snapshot. Opportunistic sharing, not a backup."},"134":{"id":"/concepts/federation-30","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"A leader among sometimes-offline laptops means stalling or failover; a lock puts a round trip on the write path. CRDT joins are commutative, associative, idempotent — duplicate, reordered, weeks-late messages converge: **strong eventual consistency**, no coordination."},"135":{"id":"/concepts/federation-31","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"Field"},"136":{"id":"/concepts/federation-32","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"Join"},"137":{"id":"/concepts/federation-33","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`access_count`, `traversal_count`"},"138":{"id":"/concepts/federation-34","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"per-replica-slot max (G-Counter)"},"139":{"id":"/concepts/federation-35","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`heat`"},"140":{"id":"/concepts/federation-36","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"max — moot, remote heat is zeroed at the boundary"},"141":{"id":"/concepts/federation-37","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`created_at`"},"142":{"id":"/concepts/federation-38","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"min — earliest observation wins"},"143":{"id":"/concepts/federation-39","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`accessed_at`, `updated_at`"},"144":{"id":"/concepts/federation-40","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"max"},"145":{"id":"/concepts/federation-41","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`valid_until`, reason score"},"146":{"id":"/concepts/federation-42","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"last-write-wins"},"147":{"id":"/concepts/federation-43","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"statement text"},"148":{"id":"/concepts/federation-44","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"**never imported** — content-addressing forbids it"},"149":{"id":"/concepts/federation-45","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"`status`"},"150":{"id":"/concepts/federation-46","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"monotone toward `Superseded`, never back"},"151":{"id":"/concepts/federation-47","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"confidence"},"152":{"id":"/concepts/federation-48","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"**never imported**"},"153":{"id":"/concepts/federation-49","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"Content-hash ids make this hold at the graph level: the same fact learned independently has the same id, existence is set union — a peer contributes ids, never mutates or deletes yours."},"154":{"id":"/concepts/federation-50","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#why-a-crdt-and-not-a-leader","content":"Confidence is the deliberate exception: a max-join would be an irreversible poisoning pin. Trust stays replica-local."},"155":{"id":"/concepts/federation-51","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#contradicting-facts-on-two-machines","content":"**The CRDT does not resolve them — by design.** Different content = different ids; both daemons hold both claims. Resolution is the same local machinery — supersession and validity windows (Time). Federation adds only:"},"156":{"id":"/concepts/federation-52","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#contradicting-facts-on-two-machines","content":"Supersession is monotone and one-way — superseded anywhere, superseded everywhere, never flipped back."},"157":{"id":"/concepts/federation-53","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#contradicting-facts-on-two-machines","content":"`superseded_by` converges deterministically (lexically greater id wins — a tiebreak for agreement, not correctness)."},"158":{"id":"/concepts/federation-54","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#contradicting-facts-on-two-machines","content":"Confidence never crosses the wire, so each daemon decides its own belief. Federation makes both claims *visible* everywhere; it does not make belief uniform."},"159":{"id":"/concepts/federation-55","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#remote-data-is-quarantined","content":"Inbound entities merge into a phantom `remote-<network>-<kern>` namespace, never your own kerns, with ranking signals stripped on entry — heat and access zeroed, confidence reset to neutral. An id already owned by a different kern is rejected as a hijack; each remote namespace caps at 50,000 entities."},"160":{"id":"/concepts/federation-56","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#remote-data-is-quarantined","content":"Raw TCP gossip, plaintext UDP discovery — no peer authentication, no signatures, no encryption. &#x2A;*Anyone who can reach the gossip port can read your federated graph in cleartext and inject entities into it.** `network_id` is not a credential — it is broadcast in the clear."},"161":{"id":"/concepts/federation-57","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#remote-data-is-quarantined","content":"Acceptable: a segment where you trust every host — home or lab LAN, private VPC subnet, WireGuard mesh (also the only confidentiality today). Firewall the gossip TCP and discovery UDP ports; bind `addr` to a private interface, not the default `0.0.0.0:7400`."},"162":{"id":"/concepts/federation-58","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#remote-data-is-quarantined","content":"Unacceptable: any public interface, coffee-shop or hotel networks, a shared office VLAN, anything internet-reachable. Full trust model: Security."},"163":{"id":"/concepts/federation-59","page_id":"/concepts/federation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/federation#turning-it-on","content":"`[gossip]` block (Configure): `enabled = true`, a shared `network_id` across the daemons to pair, prefer an explicit `peers` list over discovery. Then re-read the callout above and confirm the segment qualifies."},"164":{"id":"/concepts/graph","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"page","content":"The graph: nodes, edges, claims","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph"},"165":{"id":"/concepts/graph-0","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#why-a-graph-not-a-vector-store","content":"Why a graph, not a vector store"},"166":{"id":"/concepts/graph-1","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Thoughts"},"167":{"id":"/concepts/graph-2","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Justified edges"},"168":{"id":"/concepts/graph-3","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#claims-not-raw-transcripts","content":"Claims, not raw transcripts"},"169":{"id":"/concepts/graph-4","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#identity-content-hashes","content":"Identity: content hashes"},"170":{"id":"/concepts/graph-5","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#the-kern-tree","content":"The kern tree"},"171":{"id":"/concepts/graph-6","page_id":"/concepts/graph","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/graph#storage","content":"Storage"},"172":{"id":"/concepts/graph-7","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph","content":"Memory is a graph: *thoughts* connected by *justified edges*, held in a tree of kerns, persisted to one LMDB file. The data model every other page assumes."},"173":{"id":"/concepts/graph-8","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#why-a-graph-not-a-vector-store","content":"Similarity is symmetric, unlabelled, query-time only. A kern edge is a stored, typed, directional assertion. Buys:"},"174":{"id":"/concepts/graph-9","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#why-a-graph-not-a-vector-store","content":"**Traversal** — retrieval expands from seeds along edges; a non-matching thought is reachable through one that matches. (Reaching is not yet ranking — caveat in Retrieval.)"},"175":{"id":"/concepts/graph-10","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#why-a-graph-not-a-vector-store","content":"**Explanation** — edges carry a written reason; results return the chain walked."},"176":{"id":"/concepts/graph-11","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#why-a-graph-not-a-vector-store","content":"**Non-similar relations** — \"deadline is March\" / \"deadline is April\": near-identical vectors, opposite meanings — stored explicitly as a supersede edge. See Time."},"177":{"id":"/concepts/graph-12","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"One atomic unit of memory; `kind` decides treatment:"},"178":{"id":"/concepts/graph-13","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Kind"},"179":{"id":"/concepts/graph-14","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Meaning"},"180":{"id":"/concepts/graph-15","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"`Fact`"},"181":{"id":"/concepts/graph-16","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Durable assertion from a trusted source. Never auto-forgotten while active."},"182":{"id":"/concepts/graph-17","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"`Claim`"},"183":{"id":"/concepts/graph-18","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"The default. Distilled from a session; may or may not survive."},"184":{"id":"/concepts/graph-19","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"`Document`"},"185":{"id":"/concepts/graph-20","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"A chunk of an ingested source document."},"186":{"id":"/concepts/graph-21","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"`Question` / `Conclusion`"},"187":{"id":"/concepts/graph-22","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Internal-only — seeded and resolved by the system itself."},"188":{"id":"/concepts/graph-23","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Callers may supply only `Fact` and `Claim` (rest rejected at the MCP surface); `Fact` additionally requires a trusted source (user or agent, not an arbitrary file)."},"189":{"id":"/concepts/graph-24","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"Also on a thought:"},"190":{"id":"/concepts/graph-25","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"**Confidence** — Beta distribution; corroborations and contradictions are observations, so a claim seen five times outranks one seen once."},"191":{"id":"/concepts/graph-26","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"**Heat + access counts** — drive eviction; see Heat."},"192":{"id":"/concepts/graph-27","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"**Two vectors** — content embedding + structural embedding recomputed from the neighbourhood; retrieval blends both."},"193":{"id":"/concepts/graph-28","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"**Validity window + status** (`Active`/`Superseded`) — bi-temporal machinery; see Time."},"194":{"id":"/concepts/graph-29","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#thoughts","content":"**Provenance** — typed source: file, ticket, session, agent, or inline."},"195":{"id":"/concepts/graph-30","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`from` → `to`, with a kind, optional explanatory text, own vector:"},"196":{"id":"/concepts/graph-31","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Kind"},"197":{"id":"/concepts/graph-32","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Meaning"},"198":{"id":"/concepts/graph-33","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`Similarity`"},"199":{"id":"/concepts/graph-34","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Attached at commit to the nearest neighbour — no thought is isolated."},"200":{"id":"/concepts/graph-35","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`Provenance`"},"201":{"id":"/concepts/graph-36","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Thought → its source document."},"202":{"id":"/concepts/graph-37","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`Supersedes`"},"203":{"id":"/concepts/graph-38","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"New revision → the one it replaced."},"204":{"id":"/concepts/graph-39","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`Rephrase`"},"205":{"id":"/concepts/graph-40","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Same thought, different wording; alternate phrasing lives in the edge text."},"206":{"id":"/concepts/graph-41","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"`Question` / `Spawn` / `Ratification`"},"207":{"id":"/concepts/graph-42","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#justified-edges","content":"Question linkage, kern lineage, corroboration."},"208":{"id":"/concepts/graph-43","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#claims-not-raw-transcripts","content":"A transcript in `.kern/intake/` is never stored as memory. One LLM pass distills typed claims — atomic (independently retrievable, supersedable), typed at birth (kind-aware retention), deduplicated against everything known. Empty distillation archives the delta; no output at all (outage) leaves it queued for retry — nothing silently lost. See Acceptance."},"209":{"id":"/concepts/graph-44","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#identity-content-hashes","content":"Id = SHA-256 of the text."},"210":{"id":"/concepts/graph-45","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#identity-content-hashes","content":"Identical content = same node everywhere, forever. Federation merge is set union — no coordinator."},"211":{"id":"/concepts/graph-46","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#identity-content-hashes","content":"**Text and vector never overwritten under an existing id** — a near-duplicate with different phrasing gets a `Rephrase` edge; the tick decides contradiction later."},"212":{"id":"/concepts/graph-47","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#identity-content-hashes","content":"A duplicate (cosine above the preset's dedup threshold — 0.98 on default `relaxed`) is not discarded: it bumps the existing thought's confidence."},"213":{"id":"/concepts/graph-48","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#the-kern-tree","content":"Thoughts live in `Kern` containers in a tree. A named kern has a **graviton** — label, centroid vector, mass (default 1.0). Routing descends by `cosine_distance / mass` — a heavier graviton attracts more strongly. The root never holds thoughts; no match falls to a `generic` catch-all. See Acceptance."},"214":{"id":"/concepts/graph-49","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#storage","content":"One LMDB environment per data directory, three tables: kern rows, cold tier, graph metadata. Values are versioned zstd — an older reader rejects a newer file rather than misparsing it."},"215":{"id":"/concepts/graph-50","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#storage","content":"**Int8-quantized vectors** on disk (\\~4× smaller); structural vectors recomputed, not persisted."},"216":{"id":"/concepts/graph-51","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#storage","content":"**Epoch-guarded writes** — a stale in-memory snapshot never overwrites newer disk state."},"217":{"id":"/concepts/graph-52","page_id":"/concepts/graph","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/graph#storage","content":"**Two tiers** — GC spills to the cold tier *before* dropping from memory; a failed spill keeps it hot. Cold tier: capped (50,000 entries), unindexed tail, searched only when the hot graph comes up short. Active `Fact`s and `Document`s never evicted. Past the cap the oldest rows genuinely go — each drop counted by `health`."},"218":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"page","content":"Heat, decay & self-compaction","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction"},"219":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-0","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#heat","content":"Heat"},"220":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-1","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#decay-is-lazy","content":"Decay is lazy"},"221":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-2","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"The tick"},"222":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-3","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#clustering","content":"Clustering"},"223":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-4","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"Eviction"},"224":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-5","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#spill-before-drop","content":"Spill before drop"},"225":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-6","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-guarantee-precisely","content":"The guarantee, precisely"},"226":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-7","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#steady-state","content":"Steady state"},"227":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-8","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#see-also","content":"See also"},"228":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-9","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","content":"One scalar per thought — *heat* — exponential decay, and a background tick that reorganises the graph and evicts what has gone cold, spilling to a cold tier first: eviction is a demotion, not a deletion. No manual gardening."},"229":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-10","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#heat","content":"Dimensionless usage signal; one deposit:"},"230":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-11","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#heat","content":"**Access** — a query returning a thought deposits 1.0 and stamps `accessed_at`. Nothing else deposits. The maintenance pulse walks the tree to schedule work, not to reinforce: it did deposit until it was measured, and because the deposit recurred every tick it settled orders of magnitude above the eviction floor, exempting everything within its reach from collection whether or not anyone used it. Survival is usage, never tree position."},"231":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-12","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#heat","content":"Half-life is preset-owned: `relaxed` 30 days (default), `medium` 7 days, `tight` 3 days. No `[heat]` section to set."},"232":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-13","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#heat","content":"On the way down it enqueues clustering for every non-empty kern — naming, enrichment, question resolution on a graph nobody is querying."},"233":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-14","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#decay-is-lazy","content":"Never decremented on a timer. Stored value written only on deposit; every read computes"},"234":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-15","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#decay-is-lazy","content":"A deposit decays first, then adds — touching a stale thought does not resurrect its old magnitude. GC ages the value *before* comparing — no evading eviction on a stale stored number."},"235":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-16","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"Every 60 seconds (`tick.interval_secs`; 0 disables):"},"236":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-17","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"Reconcile with the store (concurrent writers)."},"237":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-18","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"Pulse the root."},"238":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-19","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"Fan clustering out to every non-empty kern."},"239":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-20","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"Snapshot if anything changed — crash loss bounded to one interval."},"240":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-21","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-tick","content":"A panicking task costs that task, not the loop — logged, counted, reported by `health` (`task_panics` / `task_failures`; a climbing failure count means a task gives up every beat). Hourly, not per beat: stigmergy GC and disk consolidation; both refuse to run under an unreadable or skewed clock."},"241":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-22","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#clustering","content":"The structural half of compaction. Per kern, the tick groups sampled thoughts by cosine; a cluster becomes its own child kern when the parent is named, the cluster is not restating the parent's graviton, size ≥ 10, cohesion ≥ 0.60. A cohesive child gets LLM-named — a graviton, a real routing target. Reverse in the same pass: unnamed, empty children fold back into their parent."},"242":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-23","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"A GC victim only when **all three** hold:"},"243":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-24","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"**Not durable** — active `Fact`s and `Document`s immune; supersession revokes the immunity."},"244":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-25","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"**Cold** — age-decayed heat below 0.01."},"245":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-26","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"**Stale** — untouched for more than 7 days."},"246":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-27","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#eviction","content":"Missing or future timestamp (clock skew) = *not* a victim — the predicate fails closed."},"247":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-28","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#spill-before-drop","content":"Victim written to the cold LMDB table *first*; dropped from the hot graph only on success — a failed spill stays hot for the next hourly pass. Cold rows backfill queries returning fewer than `k` hot results; bi-temporal stamps kept, so `as_of` stays exact over the cold tail."},"248":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-29","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-guarantee-precisely","content":"**Absolute:** an active `Fact` or `Document` is never collected — no heat or age overrides the kind check. A *superseded* fact loses the exemption (excluded from live recall anyway; still spilled, not erased)."},"249":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-30","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-guarantee-precisely","content":"**Bounded:** everything else survives on usage. RAM eviction is lossless; cold eviction is FIFO capped at 50,000 entries. A never-touched non-durable thought behind 50k newer entries is genuinely gone — each drop counted (`cold_evicted` on `health`)."},"250":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-31","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-guarantee-precisely","content":"No store bound → no spill; the victim is simply removed. Spill-before-drop holds only for a persisted kern."},"251":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-32","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#the-guarantee-precisely","content":"Unconditional survival: ingest as a `Document`, keep it warm, or make it a `Fact` — a CLI-only lever (kind derives from confidence, `Fact` needs full confidence, only `kern ingest` writing as the user reaches it; MCP callers clamped below)."},"252":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-33","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#steady-state","content":"Working set — queried within 6.64 half-lives, and nothing else — stays hot and indexed. Cohesive clusters condense into named kerns. Hourly drain moves untouched claims cold. Facts and documents accumulate, never swept. The hot graph tracks what you *use*, not what you have written."},"253":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-34","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#see-also","content":"Stigmergy GC & gravitons — the GC as a usage-trace, plus the attractors that bias survival."},"254":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-35","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#see-also","content":"Time — why a superseded fact loses GC immunity."},"255":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-36","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#see-also","content":"Retrieval — how heat and access feed ranking."},"256":{"id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction-37","page_id":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/heat-and-compaction#see-also","content":"Configure — the presets that own the heat knobs."},"257":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"page","content":"The retrieval pipeline","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval"},"258":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-0","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"Stages"},"259":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-1","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Indexes"},"260":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-2","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval#structural-vector","content":"Structural vector"},"261":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-3","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval#measurement","content":"Measurement"},"262":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-4","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"Related"},"263":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-5","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval","content":"A query seeds candidates from three sources (dense vectors, BM25, importance scan), fuses them by rank, walks the reason graph, then boosts, filters, diversifies. LLM-free except embedding the query text — no HyDE, no rerank, no synthesis; the caller gets scored thoughts, edges, and path chains, and synthesizes itself."},"264":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-6","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Dense seeding** — content-vector index + structural (GNN) index, blended 0.4/0.6 (fixed constant, not tuned). Query filters (kind, source, confidence, time window) applied *during* ANN traversal — a filtered top-15 is actually 15."},"265":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-7","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Lexical seeding** — BM25 over an in-RAM inverted index. Catches the literal tokens embedders smooth away: identifiers, error codes, version strings."},"266":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-8","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Importance scan** — query-independent third source: anything over a low cosine floor that is a `Fact` or accessed 3+ times. O(N) per query (the clearest scaling gap); down-weighted so popular-but-irrelevant cannot ride to the top."},"267":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-9","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**PageRank** — personalized: teleport to the query's seeds, damping 0.85. What the matching neighbourhood keeps pointing at — a signal cosine cannot produce. Rationale: PageRank for authority."},"268":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-10","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**RRF fusion** — by rank, not score: BM25, cosine, and rank mass are not comparable numbers, so no normalization to tune or break."},"269":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-11","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Expansion** — bounded beam search over reason edges from every seed; each surviving path returned as a chain of entities and labelled edges."},"270":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-12","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Merge + boosts** — corroboration bonus for entities found by two routes; then score × confidence, an access/recency term, a flat `Fact` bonus, graviton pull (max over gravitons — no double-count)."},"271":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-13","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Filter, dedup, MMR** — superseded dropped; delivery floor applies unless nothing clears it (weak results over nothing); same-section chunks collapse to their best; MMR λ 0.75."},"272":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-14","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"**Cold backfill** — fewer than `k` hot results scans the cold tier, flags hits `cold:true`; `as_of` stays exact over backfill."},"273":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-15","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#stages","content":"Measured, not suspected: over 8 linked A→B pairs probed with text matching only A, the edge moves one pair by one rank. An entity reached both by content and across an edge keeps the larger of its two scores — the edge contributes nothing. &#x2A;*No claim that traversal improves what is recalled is true today.** Item 86 in `ROADMAP.md`."},"274":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-16","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Index"},"275":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-17","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Notes"},"276":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-18","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"HNSW"},"277":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-19","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Resident, the default. Memory for latency; rebuilt on load."},"278":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-20","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"DiskANN"},"279":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-21","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Opt-in via `[graph] disk_threshold`, off by default. Mmapped disk graph for kerns too big to stay resident; held to recall\\@10 ≥ 0.90 vs brute force. DiskANN-style spill."},"280":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-22","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"BM25"},"281":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-23","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"In-RAM inverted index; memory proportional to vocabulary."},"282":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-24","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#indexes","content":"Vectors stored int8-quantized (4× smaller); a test pins int8 top-10 agreement with full-precision float at ≥ 75%. Binary quantization exists but is deliberately not user-selectable — recall floor too low without a rescoring pass."},"283":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-25","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#structural-vector","content":"A background tick trains a small per-kern GNN over the real reason edges, writing each thought a second, structural vector — thoughts that never share vocabulary drift together if the graph keeps connecting them. Weighted 0.6 in dense seeding. Needs 128+ thoughts in a kern; the most expensive background cost."},"284":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-26","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#measurement","content":"e2e drives `kern query` over a self-authored corpus with no LLM in scoring: recall\\@1 **0.9583**, recall\\@5 **1.0000**, MRR **0.9792** (2026-07-21, reproducible bit-for-bit). Two limits travel with it:"},"285":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-27","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#measurement","content":"Floors sit below the measured values — a **regression detector**: says kern got worse, never that kern is good."},"286":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-28","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#measurement","content":"Embedder is a deterministic feature-hashed bag of words — measures kern's machinery over a fixed lexical signal, not an embedding model's semantics."},"287":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-29","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#measurement","content":"No number here is comparable to anything Zep, Mem0, or Letta publish — different corpus, embedder, scoring. kern makes **no quality claim of any kind**. Never quote a retrieval number that did not come from a run."},"288":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-30","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"The graph — the structure retrieval walks."},"289":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-31","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"Acceptance — how thoughts get in."},"290":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-32","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"Time — why superseded thoughts never seed; `as_of`."},"291":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-33","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"Heat & compaction — where access counts come from."},"292":{"id":"/concepts/retrieval-34","page_id":"/concepts/retrieval","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/retrieval#related","content":"Configure — the knobs."},"293":{"id":"/concepts/security","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"page","content":"Security","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security"},"294":{"id":"/concepts/security-0","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#nothing-listens-by-default","content":"Nothing listens by default"},"295":{"id":"/concepts/security-1","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#data-at-rest-is-plaintext","content":"Data at rest is plaintext"},"296":{"id":"/concepts/security-2","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"What leaves the machine"},"297":{"id":"/concepts/security-3","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#keys-do-not-follow-a-redirected-endpoint","content":"Keys do not follow a redirected endpoint"},"298":{"id":"/concepts/security-4","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"The federation trust model"},"299":{"id":"/concepts/security-5","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"What a malicious peer can and cannot do"},"300":{"id":"/concepts/security-6","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#deployment-guidance","content":"Deployment guidance"},"301":{"id":"/concepts/security-7","page_id":"/concepts/security","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/security#reporting","content":"Reporting"},"302":{"id":"/concepts/security-8","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security","content":"The trust model as implemented today: what the daemon exposes locally, what leaves the machine, and what a network peer can and cannot do once federation is enabled — including the parts that protect nothing."},"303":{"id":"/concepts/security-9","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security","content":"**A default kern opens no network port** — RPC over an owner-only Unix socket, MCP over stdio, gossip off."},"304":{"id":"/concepts/security-10","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security","content":"**Memory is plaintext on disk** in `.kern/data` — treat it like the source tree it describes."},"305":{"id":"/concepts/security-11","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security","content":"**Everything kern captures transits your LLM endpoints** — localhost Ollama by default. Pointing them at a hosted API is your configuration decision, not a kern default."},"306":{"id":"/concepts/security-12","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security","content":"**Federation, when enabled, is unauthenticated and unencrypted** — treat the gossip segment like an unauthenticated internal Redis."},"307":{"id":"/concepts/security-13","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#nothing-listens-by-default","content":"**RPC socket** — Unix domain socket, mode `0600`. That permission is the entire access-control story: the socket serves unauthenticated reads and mutations, so only the owning user may reach it."},"308":{"id":"/concepts/security-14","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#nothing-listens-by-default","content":"**MCP** — stdio by default; no listener. MCP-over-HTTP is opt-in and never unauthenticated: bearer token from config or a per-graph token file minted `0600` on first use; remote callers without it get a 401."},"309":{"id":"/concepts/security-15","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#nothing-listens-by-default","content":"Local attack surface reduces to filesystem access: anyone who can read your files can read your memory; anyone who cannot, cannot reach the daemon either."},"310":{"id":"/concepts/security-16","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#data-at-rest-is-plaintext","content":"`.kern/data/data.mdb` is unencrypted. No at-rest encryption planned at this layer: the memory is exactly as sensitive as the code and conversations it was distilled from, which sit unencrypted in the same tree — encrypting one beside the other is theater. If the disk needs protection, full-disk encryption protects both."},"311":{"id":"/concepts/security-17","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#data-at-rest-is-plaintext","content":"Also under `.kern/data`: the MCP token file (`0600`), and `logs/*.log` — owner-only, append-only, and at `RUST_LOG=debug` they can include graph content. Back up or sync `.kern/` with the same policy as a private repo."},"312":{"id":"/concepts/security-18","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"**LLM endpoints — always, by design.** Every captured text is embedded; distillation and enrichment send memory content as prompt context."},"313":{"id":"/concepts/security-19","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Leg"},"314":{"id":"/concepts/security-20","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Default URL"},"315":{"id":"/concepts/security-21","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Default model"},"316":{"id":"/concepts/security-22","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Embedding"},"317":{"id":"/concepts/security-23","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"`http://localhost:11434`"},"318":{"id":"/concepts/security-24","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"`qwen3-embedding:0.6b`"},"319":{"id":"/concepts/security-25","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Reason"},"320":{"id":"/concepts/security-26","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"`http://localhost:11434`"},"321":{"id":"/concepts/security-27","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"`granite4:3b`"},"322":{"id":"/concepts/security-28","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"Defaults keep everything on localhost. Redirecting to a hosted API is the single largest data-flow decision an operator makes; kern deliberately does not make it for you."},"323":{"id":"/concepts/security-29","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-leaves-the-machine","content":"**The gossip seed — never, unless opted in twice.** Dialed only when both `gossip.enabled` and `gossip.seed` are true."},"324":{"id":"/concepts/security-30","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#keys-do-not-follow-a-redirected-endpoint","content":"Config scopes deep-merge per key, so a project `.kern/kern.toml` inherits user-level settings — a cloned repo committing `[embed] url = \"http://attacker.example\"` could harvest your inherited API key on the first embed call. One deliberate exception: &#x2A;*a scope that sets a section's `url` does not inherit that section's `key`.** The redirect applies; the credential is withheld. A mitigation, not a sandbox — a project config can still send your memory to any endpoint it names, but not with a credential minted for a different one."},"325":{"id":"/concepts/security-31","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Applies only after `[gossip] enabled = true`. Raw TCP plus plaintext UDP discovery — no encryption, no authentication, no signatures. Sniffing the segment reads every shared thought; reaching the port speaks the protocol."},"326":{"id":"/concepts/security-32","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"**Why no authentication yet:** signatures without an identity scheme (key generation, distribution, revocation across multicast-discovered daemons) are worthless, and a half-measure would imply safety the protocol does not provide. Interim rule: **run gossip only on a segment where you trust every host**; get confidentiality from the network layer (WireGuard, VPN). `network_id` is a grouping key broadcast in cleartext, not a credential."},"327":{"id":"/concepts/security-33","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Structural bounds, one principle: your local graph records what *you* learned; no remote assertion may alter it or buy ranking influence inside it."},"328":{"id":"/concepts/security-34","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Remote entities quarantined in `remote-*` phantom kerns, never your own."},"329":{"id":"/concepts/security-35","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Content-hash ids: merge is set union; an id owned by a different kern is rejected as a hijack."},"330":{"id":"/concepts/security-36","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Ranking signals stripped at the boundary — heat and access zeroed, confidence reset to neutral."},"331":{"id":"/concepts/security-37","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Confidence never merges in either direction — a max-join would be an irreversible poisoning pin."},"332":{"id":"/concepts/security-38","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Statement text never merges — a same-id peer has identical content by construction; a differing one is lying about its hash."},"333":{"id":"/concepts/security-39","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"Flood limits: 50k entities per remote namespace, 4 MB frame cap, per-message counter clamps, bounded dedup set, 50-peer table."},"334":{"id":"/concepts/security-40","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#the-federation-trust-model","content":"A poisoned message kills its own connection task, not the daemon."},"335":{"id":"/concepts/security-41","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"A peer on the segment **can**"},"336":{"id":"/concepts/security-42","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Bound"},"337":{"id":"/concepts/security-43","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Read every broadcast; fetch any entity body by id"},"338":{"id":"/concepts/security-44","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"none — the read surface is open"},"339":{"id":"/concepts/security-45","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Inject entities with arbitrary text"},"340":{"id":"/concepts/security-46","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"quarantined, capped, ranking-stripped — but vector-indexed, so retrievable"},"341":{"id":"/concepts/security-47","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Probe whether you hold a fact near a given vector"},"342":{"id":"/concepts/security-48","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"0.80 similarity threshold"},"343":{"id":"/concepts/security-49","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Inflate access/traversal counters on local rows"},"344":{"id":"/concepts/security-50","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"clamped per message; replica names attacker-chosen"},"345":{"id":"/concepts/security-51","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Set reason scores and `valid_until` on local rows"},"346":{"id":"/concepts/security-52","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"LWW; a poisoned `valid_until` bites only callers passing `valid_at` — today"},"347":{"id":"/concepts/security-53","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Drive maintenance work with `Pulse`"},"348":{"id":"/concepts/security-54","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"id must name a `remote-*` kern you already hold, strength clamped; deposits no heat"},"349":{"id":"/concepts/security-55","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Impersonate any `network_id`"},"350":{"id":"/concepts/security-56","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"by design — not a credential"},"351":{"id":"/concepts/security-57","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"A peer **cannot**"},"352":{"id":"/concepts/security-58","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Why"},"353":{"id":"/concepts/security-59","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Alter or delete the text of any entity you hold"},"354":{"id":"/concepts/security-60","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"statement text never merges"},"355":{"id":"/concepts/security-61","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Claim an id owned by one of your local kerns"},"356":{"id":"/concepts/security-62","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"hijack guard"},"357":{"id":"/concepts/security-63","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Raise the confidence of anything"},"358":{"id":"/concepts/security-64","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"confidence never crosses the wire"},"359":{"id":"/concepts/security-65","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Give its injected entities heat or access history"},"360":{"id":"/concepts/security-66","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"stripped at the boundary"},"361":{"id":"/concepts/security-67","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Grow a remote namespace past 50k entities"},"362":{"id":"/concepts/security-68","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"cap"},"363":{"id":"/concepts/security-69","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Crash the daemon with one malformed message"},"364":{"id":"/concepts/security-70","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"task-per-connection, non-poisoning locks"},"365":{"id":"/concepts/security-71","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#what-a-malicious-peer-can-and-cannot-do","content":"Residuals: enabling gossip lets every host on the segment read what kern knows and place retrievable text into your recall results (flagged `remote-*`, ranking-stripped, but present) — if recall feeds an agent, federation extends that agent's context to every host on the segment. A peer can also heat your local graph and expire local claims via LWW deltas; quarantine bounds the damage, it does not make a peer harmless."},"366":{"id":"/concepts/security-72","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#deployment-guidance","content":"**Acceptable:** a home or lab LAN you control; a private VPC subnet with the gossip TCP and discovery UDP ports closed to the fleet; a WireGuard-style mesh (the only source of confidentiality and peer authentication today)."},"367":{"id":"/concepts/security-73","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#deployment-guidance","content":"**Unacceptable:** any public interface (bind `addr` to a private interface — the default is `0.0.0.0:7400`); coffee-shop or hotel Wi-Fi; a shared office VLAN; any segment carrying hosts you would not allow to read your working memory and inject text into your agent's recall."},"368":{"id":"/concepts/security-74","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#deployment-guidance","content":"Distinct `network_id` per deployment, explicit `peers` list over discovery, `seed = false`. No multi-node need → leave gossip off (the default) and this page's network section exits your threat model. See Configure."},"369":{"id":"/concepts/security-75","page_id":"/concepts/security","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/security#reporting","content":"Report security issues privately via GitHub security advisories before public disclosure, with the observed behavior and where you believe the fault lies."},"370":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"page","content":"Stigmergy GC & gravitons","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy"},"371":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-0","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-metaphor","content":"The metaphor"},"372":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-1","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-trace","content":"The trace"},"373":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-2","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#from-trace-to-collection","content":"From trace to collection"},"374":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-3","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"Gravitons"},"375":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-4","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#auto-promotion-out-of-generic","content":"Auto-promotion out of `generic`"},"376":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-5","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#why-plural-not-singular","content":"Why plural, not singular"},"377":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-6","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#observing-and-forcing-it","content":"Observing and forcing it"},"378":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-7","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/stigmergy#see-also","content":"See also"},"379":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-8","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy","content":"kern forgets from the traces reads leave behind, not from a retention policy anyone wrote. This page: that trace, and gravitons — named, weighted attractors biasing which regions stay dense and which results surface first."},"380":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-9","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-metaphor","content":"Ants deposit pheromone; other ants prefer marked paths; pheromone evaporates — the route emerges from the medium. That is stigmergy. The loan ends there: kern's mechanism is exponential decay plus a threshold test. Why this over scheduled cleanup: Stigmergy over gardening."},"381":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-10","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-trace","content":"**Reads deposit** — a returned thought gets an access-count bump, an `accessed_at` stamp, a heat deposit. Deferred to the tick — recall never blocks on a write, never counts as content mutation."},"382":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-11","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-trace","content":"**The pulse does not deposit** — it walks from the root at half strength per level to *schedule* work, and lays no pheromone. It used to, and a deposit that recurs every tick never evaporates: everything the walk reached became permanently uncollectible. An idle daemon still maintains itself, on the clustering fan-out, not on manufactured heat."},"383":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-12","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#the-trace","content":"**Evaporation** — exponential, lazy, from the age of the last deposit. See Heat & compaction."},"384":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-13","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#from-trace-to-collection","content":"Hourly, per kern: collect every thought that is **not durable** (active `Fact`/`Document` immune), **cold** (aged heat below 0.01), and **stale** (untouched > 7 days) — spilling each to the cold tier before dropping. Full guarantee: Heat & compaction."},"385":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-14","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#from-trace-to-collection","content":"No LRU list, no quota, no \"keep the last N\" — a pure predicate over values already maintained for ranking. Retention emerges from usage, not administration."},"386":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-15","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"Heat says what has been *used*; gravitons say what the graph is *for* — set deliberately."},"387":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-16","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"A graviton: name, pull vector, scalar `mass` (default 1.0). Manage with the `graviton` MCP tool (`action=list|add|remove`). Seed text: **example statements, one per line** — each line embedded separately, mean = pull vector. Measured: pooled examples sit markedly closer to held-out same-focus claims than an abstract description. Keep each line under the embedding model's context window."},"388":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-17","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"Two action points:"},"389":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-18","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"**Ingest** — routing picks the child nearest by `cosine_distance / mass`; no match falls to the `generic` catch-all."},"390":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-19","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"**Query** — boost proportional to best graviton match × mass (**max**, not sum — overlapping gravitons never double-count). Default weight 0.15; 0 disables; a graviton-free graph pays nothing."},"391":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-20","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#gravitons","content":"Heat and gravitons are not wired together and do not compound: a graviton biases what is *found*, and being found is what deposits heat. Position in the tree buys nothing on its own — aiming a graviton is a statement about what the graph should surface, and retention follows only if surfacing turns into use."},"392":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-21","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#auto-promotion-out-of-generic","content":"When the tick names a kern under `generic` and no equivalent root graviton exists, it is reparented to the root — a new graviton nobody declared in advance."},"393":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-22","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#why-plural-not-singular","content":"Gravitons replaced a single per-kern `purpose` field. One purpose forces one answer to \"what is this memory about\"; the plural model allows overlapping focuses, weighting between them (mass means nothing without alternatives), and a query-time bias at all. Gravity is a bias knob by design, not a measured recall improvement."},"394":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-23","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#observing-and-forcing-it","content":"`health` — graviton, kern, entity, reason counts (fastest way to spot unnamed-kern churn), plus `cold_evicted` — the one place retention stops being lossless."},"395":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-24","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#observing-and-forcing-it","content":"The `gc` tool is a *different* collector: reaps empty and orphan kerns (structure, not content)."},"396":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-25","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#observing-and-forcing-it","content":"Deleting rows frees LMDB pages, not disk size — the file compacts on restart or `kern compact`. A `gc` reaping thousands of kerns with unchanged `data.mdb` is correct."},"397":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-26","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#see-also","content":"Heat & compaction — decay, the tick, the retention guarantee in full."},"398":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-27","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#see-also","content":"Acceptance — how effective distance places a thought."},"399":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-28","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#see-also","content":"Retrieval — where gravity sits in ranking."},"400":{"id":"/concepts/stigmergy-29","page_id":"/concepts/stigmergy","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/stigmergy#see-also","content":"MCP tools — the `graviton` and `gc` surfaces."},"401":{"id":"/concepts/time","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"page","content":"Time & contradiction","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time"},"402":{"id":"/concepts/time-0","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#why-revision-is-first-class","content":"Why revision is first-class"},"403":{"id":"/concepts/time-1","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"Two clocks"},"404":{"id":"/concepts/time-2","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"Supersede"},"405":{"id":"/concepts/time-3","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#contradiction-detection","content":"Contradiction detection"},"406":{"id":"/concepts/time-4","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#querying-the-past","content":"Querying the past"},"407":{"id":"/concepts/time-5","page_id":"/concepts/time","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/time#what-time-does-not-do","content":"What time does not do"},"408":{"id":"/concepts/time-6","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time","content":"Every thought carries two clocks: when a statement was true in the world, and when kern found out. A contradicted claim is *superseded* — invalidated, kept as history — never deleted; query what was true, or what kern believed, at any instant."},"409":{"id":"/concepts/time-7","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#why-revision-is-first-class","content":"\"Deadline is March\", then \"moved to April\": a vector store holds both — near-identical embeddings, opposite meanings — and returns whichever ranks higher. Deleting the old one loses \"what did we think in January?\", the audit trail, and the evidence it moved at all."},"410":{"id":"/concepts/time-8","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"Clock"},"411":{"id":"/concepts/time-9","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"Fields"},"412":{"id":"/concepts/time-10","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"Meaning"},"413":{"id":"/concepts/time-11","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"World time"},"414":{"id":"/concepts/time-12","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"`[valid_from, valid_to)`"},"415":{"id":"/concepts/time-13","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"When the statement was true out there. Half-open — revisions tile without overlap. Distillation can extract an explicit `valid_from`."},"416":{"id":"/concepts/time-14","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"Transaction time"},"417":{"id":"/concepts/time-15","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"`created_at` / `invalidated_at`"},"418":{"id":"/concepts/time-16","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"When kern's own store changed."},"419":{"id":"/concepts/time-17","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"They come apart routinely: learn Friday about Monday's reversal; backfill six months in an afternoon; \"what did the system believe on the 3rd?\" vs \"what was true on the 3rd?\"."},"420":{"id":"/concepts/time-18","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#two-clocks","content":"A thought with no temporal information is always considered valid — the conservative default; the alternative would silently hide everything written before the temporal machinery existed."},"421":{"id":"/concepts/time-19","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"Two paths, same mutation: **explicit** re-ingest under the same external id, or a **contradiction** verdict from the tick. Either way:"},"422":{"id":"/concepts/time-20","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"New thought inserted and indexed normally."},"423":{"id":"/concepts/time-21","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"Old one's status → `Superseded`, pointing at its successor."},"424":{"id":"/concepts/time-22","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"Transaction time stamped *now*; world-time window closes when the new claim became true — clocks set independently."},"425":{"id":"/concepts/time-23","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"Old id leaves the vector indexes but stays in its kern — no longer retrieved, history recoverable."},"426":{"id":"/concepts/time-24","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#supersede","content":"A `Supersedes` edge links new to old."},"427":{"id":"/concepts/time-25","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#contradiction-detection","content":"Never at query time, never synchronously at ingest. Ingest records a `Rephrase` edge; the background tick asks the LLM one constrained question — UPDATE, CONTRADICT, or RELATED."},"428":{"id":"/concepts/time-26","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#contradiction-detection","content":"**Recall stays LLM-free** — decision made before any query arrives."},"429":{"id":"/concepts/time-27","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#contradiction-detection","content":"**Fails open to coexistence** — hedged, empty, or unparseable = RELATED. A missed contradiction leaves two coexisting claims (recoverable); a false supersede hides a true claim (not)."},"430":{"id":"/concepts/time-28","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#contradiction-detection","content":"**Kind gates the verdict** — only a same-kind near-duplicate may supersede; a distilled `Claim` never invalidates a user-asserted `Fact`."},"431":{"id":"/concepts/time-29","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#querying-the-past","content":"Two independent `query` options; they compose into the revision chain as it stood at a past instant:"},"432":{"id":"/concepts/time-30","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#querying-the-past","content":"**`as_of <timestamp>`** — pure world-time filter: the single revision whose validity window covered that instant. Exact over the cold tier too."},"433":{"id":"/concepts/time-31","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#querying-the-past","content":"**`include_history`** — normal query, then walks the supersede chain backward from each hit; ancestors flagged `history:true` (recovered from cold if needed). Widens results without loosening filters."},"434":{"id":"/concepts/time-32","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#querying-the-past","content":"`as_of` ≠ `valid_at`. `valid_at` checks an explicit expiry date stamped on a thought; `as_of` checks the supersede-maintained validity window. A claim can be unexpired yet superseded, and vice versa."},"435":{"id":"/concepts/time-33","page_id":"/concepts/time","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/time#what-time-does-not-do","content":"Bi-temporality governs *correctness* (which revision is current), not *retention*. A superseded thought must still go cold before GC touches it — supersession only makes it eligible (revokes a `Fact`'s eviction immunity). A queried superseded claim stays hot; an untouched uncontradicted one goes cold. See Heat & compaction."},"436":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","type":"page","content":"Why kern exists","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Concepts"],"tags":[],"url":"/concepts/why-kern"},"437":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-0","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Where chunk-embed-retrieve breaks"},"438":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-1","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/why-kern#the-trade","content":"The trade"},"439":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-2","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/why-kern#maturity","content":"Maturity"},"440":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-3","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/concepts/why-kern#next","content":"Next"},"441":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-4","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern","content":"Agent sessions forget — the next one re-asks settled questions, re-proposes rejected approaches. kern is a memory daemon: a self-maintaining knowledge graph per project, served back in under a millisecond with no LLM call at recall time."},"442":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-5","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"RAG (chunk, embed, prepend top-k) has four structural gaps no `k` closes:"},"443":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-6","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Gap"},"444":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-7","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"kern's answer"},"445":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-8","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Page"},"446":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-9","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"No supersede — a stale chunk embeds as close as the current one"},"447":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-10","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Bi-temporal claims: contradicted claim is **superseded**, never deleted; query `as_of` or `include_history`."},"448":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-11","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Time"},"449":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-12","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"No structure — a vector store is a flat bag"},"450":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-13","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Graph of **thoughts** linked by **reason edges** — *why*s derived at write time, walked free at query time."},"451":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-14","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Graph · Retrieval"},"452":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-15","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Unbounded growth — every chunk scored forever"},"453":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-16","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"**Heat** on access, exponential decay, stigmergy GC spilling cold thoughts to a capped cold tier. `Fact`s immune. Nobody prunes."},"454":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-17","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Heat · Stigmergy"},"455":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-18","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"No sense of what matters here"},"456":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-19","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"**Gravitons** — named focus attractors bending ingest routing and ranking. One isolated graph per working directory; `degrade` down-weights paths that produced bad answers."},"457":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-20","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Acceptance · Stigmergy"},"458":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-21","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#where-chunk-embed-retrieve-breaks","content":"Premise: memory is a process that operates itself, not an index you operate."},"459":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-22","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#the-trade","content":"**Recall costs no LLM call — you pay at write time.** Ingest distills with an LLM; contradiction checks are more LLM work in the background tick; the read path is a sub-millisecond graph walk. Write-heavy, rarely-recalling workloads get this trade backwards."},"460":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-23","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#the-trade","content":"Needs a model endpoint (local Ollama by default): an embedding model *and* a reasoning model."},"461":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-24","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#the-trade","content":"Forgets by design — an untouched non-`Fact` eventually leaves the hot graph."},"462":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-25","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#the-trade","content":"`Fact` is CLI-only (requires full confidence; only the user source reaches it). MCP durability levers: `Document`, or keep the thought warm."},"463":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-26","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#maturity","content":"`building`, not shipped; transport unauthenticated and unencrypted. See Federation and Security."},"464":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-27","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#maturity","content":"Retrieval baseline is a **regression detector, not a quality claim**: recall\\@1 0.9583, recall\\@5 1.0000, MRR 0.9792 (2026-07-21) — deterministic fake embedder, self-authored corpus; can say kern got worse, never that kern is good; comparable to nothing anyone else publishes."},"465":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-28","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#maturity","content":"**A reason edge cannot yet lift its neighbour into the results** — stored and walkable, but the walk's evidence is discarded in scoring; the multi-hop gap is not yet closed. Item 86 in `ROADMAP.md`."},"466":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-29","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#maturity","content":"Architecture implemented, self-maintenance works; hop-dependent recall not delivered yet."},"467":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-30","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#next","content":"Install & run"},"468":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-31","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#next","content":"Configure models"},"469":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-32","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#next","content":"Seed the graph"},"470":{"id":"/concepts/why-kern-33","page_id":"/concepts/why-kern","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/concepts/why-kern#next","content":"Architecture"},"471":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"page","content":"Bayesian confidence","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence"},"472":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-0","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#decision","content":"Decision"},"473":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-1","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"Why"},"474":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-2","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"475":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-3","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"476":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-4","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#where-you-see-it","content":"Where you see it"},"477":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-5","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#decision","content":"A thought's confidence is a Beta distribution — pseudo-counts `conf_alpha`/`conf_beta` updated by weighted observations, ranking multiplied by the posterior mean — not a scalar the latest writer overwrites."},"478":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-6","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#decision","content":"Ingest seeds `(α, β) = (1 + conf, 1 + (1 − conf))` — a uniform prior nudged toward the observer's stated confidence."},"479":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-7","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"kern's truth signal is convergence across independent observers; a scalar has no sample count — \"one observer, conf 0.9\" and \"twenty observers, mean 0.9\" are indistinguishable, yet warrant opposite treatment on dissent."},"480":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-8","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"Every scalar update rule fails: overwrite is last-writer-wins, max lets one overconfident source pin truth forever, averaging forgets how much evidence it stands on."},"481":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-9","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"The clamp is the outvoting property: no observation is worth more than one vote. Ten concordant observations reach mean ≈ 0.83; one full-strength dissent drops it \\~0.09 — visible, not decisive."},"482":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-10","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"Observers today:"},"483":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-11","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"Ingest dedup — a near-duplicate above the preset's dedup threshold (0.98 on default `relaxed`) adds support to the existing entity; text and vector never overwritten (id is the content hash)."},"484":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-12","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"GNN propagation — after each re-embedding pass, content-vector/structural-vector alignment supports, misalignment contradicts. The only contradiction writer."},"485":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-13","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#why","content":"Never peers — `conf_alpha`/`conf_beta` are never imported; a peer can gossip a claim, not belief in one."},"486":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-14","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"487":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-15","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"488":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-16","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Keep the scalar"},"489":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-17","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"a lone `conf=1.0` write fixes truth"},"490":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-18","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Integer support/oppose counters"},"491":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-19","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"a tentative guess and a firm assertion each count 1; no principled uncertainty"},"492":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-20","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"Full belief networks"},"493":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-21","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#rejected","content":"over-scoped; claims aren't a dependency DAG, and inference cost would sit on the ingest path"},"494":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-22","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"No `stance` parameter on ingest — disagreement requires asserting a conflicting claim and letting the classifier rule."},"495":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-23","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"No observer-reputation weighting (planned composition with PageRank authority never built on either side)."},"496":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-24","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"No evidence decay: `α` and `β` only grow, so stale consensus takes proportionally many new observations to unseat."},"497":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-25","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"Reason edges keep a plain last-writer-wins score, not a tuple."},"498":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-26","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#trade-off-accepted","content":"A same-kind near-duplicate whose text conflicts goes to an LLM classifier on\nthe background tick; an unambiguous verdict supersedes the old claim outright.\nBeta confidence answers \"how corroborated\"; supersession answers \"which\nrevision is current\". See Time & contradiction."},"499":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-27","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#where-you-see-it","content":"Corroborated claims outrank merely asserted ones, no extra machinery."},"500":{"id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence-28","page_id":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/bayesian-confidence#where-you-see-it","content":"See Acceptance & routing and The retrieval pipeline."},"501":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","type":"page","content":"CRDTs over consensus","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus"},"502":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-0","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#decision","content":"Decision"},"503":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-1","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Why"},"504":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-2","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"505":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-3","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"506":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-4","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#decision","content":"Federated state converges through per-field merge operations that commute — no leader, no lock, no consensus protocol; counters and LWW registers are live on the wire, anti-entropy is not built, federation itself off by default."},"507":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-5","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"kern daemons are laptops: they sleep, drop off, rejoin hours later. Gossip is best-effort flooding — any message can arrive late, twice, or never."},"508":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-6","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Commutative, associative, idempotent merges make the transport *allowed* to be unreliable — order and duplication stop mattering."},"509":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-7","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Target is strong eventual consistency: replicas that saw the same updates hold the same state, any order, no coordination round."},"510":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-8","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Per-field joins:"},"511":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-9","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Field"},"512":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-10","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Join"},"513":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-11","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"access / traversal counters"},"514":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-12","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"G-Counter: per-replica slot, merge = pointwise max, value = sum"},"515":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-13","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"`created_at`"},"516":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-14","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"min (earliest observation wins)"},"517":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-15","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"`accessed_at`, `updated_at`"},"518":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-16","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"max"},"519":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-17","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"edge score, `valid_until`"},"520":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-18","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"LWW on `(lamport, producer)` — never wall clock"},"521":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-19","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"`status`"},"522":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-20","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"monotone toward `Superseded`, never back"},"523":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-21","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Load-bearing details:"},"524":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-22","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"Deltas carry the sender's absolute slot total, not an increment — increments are lost if an earlier delta was missed; absolute totals self-heal."},"525":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-23","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#why","content":"LWW ties break on `(lamport, producer)`, so clock skew cannot lose an update."},"526":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-24","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"527":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-25","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"528":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-26","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Raft/Paxos leader"},"529":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-27","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"leader sleeps (laptops do) → fleet stalls or elects among unreachable peers; failover machinery for two laptops"},"530":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-28","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Distributed locks"},"531":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-29","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"network round trip on the write path; no correct behaviour when the holder is unreachable"},"532":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-30","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"Wall-clock LWW everywhere"},"533":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-31","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#rejected","content":"two concurrent `+1`s must sum to `+2` but LWW keeps one; clock skew makes \"last\" a lie"},"534":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-32","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"No anti-entropy — a replica that misses a delta stays behind until an absolute-total delta or entity sync covers the gap; entity sync carries only the hottest 32, so cold state has no bounded propagation guarantee."},"535":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-33","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"Confidence never crosses the wire — `conf_alpha`/`conf_beta` exempt from merge; a max-join on belief would be an irreversible poisoning pin."},"536":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-34","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"Statements never imported — an entity's id is the content hash of its text; a differing peer asserts text its id doesn't hash to and is rejected outright."},"537":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-35","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"CRDT semantics enforced by hand at call sites, not by typed registers."},"538":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-36","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"Convergence of state, not truth — two contradicting facts survive on both machines; adjudication belongs to supersession, not a merge thread."},"539":{"id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus-37","page_id":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/crdts-over-consensus#trade-off-accepted","content":"CRDTs guarantee convergence among honest replicas. Hostile peers are bounded\nby the inbound delta clamp, the quarantined remote namespace, and signal\nstripping at the boundary — see\nKnowledge, not gradients and\nFederation."},"540":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"page","content":"DiskANN spill for large kerns","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill"},"541":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-0","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#decision","content":"Decision"},"542":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-1","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"Why"},"543":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-2","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"544":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-3","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"545":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-4","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#where-you-see-it","content":"Where you see it"},"546":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-5","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#decision","content":"When a kern's entity count crosses a configured `disk_threshold`, its vector index spills from resident HNSW to a memory-mapped DiskANN (Vamana) snapshot with an in-RAM write delta and tombstones; the default threshold is \"never spill\", so small deployments run the resident path byte-for-byte."},"547":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-6","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"The resident index holds every vector and HNSW layer on the heap; RSS and load time grow with the corpus without bound."},"548":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-7","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"Vamana maps almost one-to-one onto existing code: single-layer, alpha-pruned proximity graph reusing HNSW's beam search and pruning — drop the layer hierarchy, put adjacency on disk."},"549":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-8","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"Snapshot is flat mmapped files (vectors + fixed-degree adjacency), size-validated on open; the OS page cache holds the vectors, not the heap."},"550":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-9","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"Build is reproducible — seeded RNG *and* order-stable containers, because the seed alone was not enough and this line claimed otherwise until 2026-07-21. Held to recall\\@10 ≥ 0.90 against brute force by an inline test — the trade is named, not assumed."},"551":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-10","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"FreshDiskANN semantics for continuous ingest: post-snapshot inserts go into a small in-RAM HNSW delta and tombstone their id; search is `(snapshot − tombstones) ∪ delta`, so new captures are searchable immediately. A tick task folds the delta into a fresh snapshot past 10,000 entries, at most hourly."},"552":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-11","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#why","content":"Any build or open failure falls back to the resident index — a disk error never breaks the graph."},"553":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-12","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"554":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-13","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"555":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-14","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Entity-eviction cap"},"556":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-15","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"silently deletes recall; the fact captured once and never yet recalled is what a memory exists to keep"},"557":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-16","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Harder quantization"},"558":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-17","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"int8 already cuts vector memory 4x, but quantization shrinks the constant, not the `O(N)` heap term; binary's recall floor needs a rescoring pass that doesn't exist"},"559":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-18","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"External vector DB / ANN library"},"560":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-19","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"violates the constraint that every retrieval stage is hand-written and inspectable; contradicts one-daemon-per-directory deployment"},"561":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-20","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"Fixing the cold tier"},"562":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-21","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#rejected","content":"the original target, dissolved before wiring landed — cold tier moved to LMDB with a bounded scan; the real ceiling was the hot resident index"},"563":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-22","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#trade-off-accepted","content":"Entity index only — GNN-vector and reason-edge indexes always rebuild resident, so a spilled kern still carries two in-RAM indexes that grow with the corpus. Measured 2026-07-21: spilling those two as well costs 122 MB more at 50k entities, so this stays a trade-off accepted rather than a gap to close (`ROADMAP.md` item 29)."},"564":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-23","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#trade-off-accepted","content":"Not answer-preserving. Spilling swaps HNSW for Vamana, so the same query can return a different top-k: recall\\@10 against brute force is 1.0000 resident vs 0.9940 spilled, with 0.9940 overlap between them (`tests/spill_transparency.rs`)."},"565":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-24","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#trade-off-accepted","content":"Full `f32` on disk, no product quantization — PQ would shrink page-cache footprint later; its open questions (codebook training, drift on model swap) stay open."},"566":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-25","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#trade-off-accepted","content":"Opt-in, not auto-tuned — an operator sets `[graph] disk_threshold` per deployment; nothing decides for you."},"567":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-26","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#where-you-see-it","content":"Crossing the threshold moves the entity vector set off the heap on the next index rebuild — but page faults *are* RAM, and the measurement says resident size does not fall: 510.3 MB resident vs 512.1 MB spilled once queries have touched the snapshot, at 50k entities. What changes is that \\~97 MB becomes clean file-backed page cache the kernel can reclaim under pressure, instead of anonymous heap it cannot."},"568":{"id":"/decisions/diskann-spill-27","page_id":"/decisions/diskann-spill","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/diskann-spill#where-you-see-it","content":"Same backend calls serve dense seeding either way — see The retrieval pipeline."},"569":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"page","content":"Edit convergence","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence"},"570":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-0","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#decision","content":"Decision"},"571":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-1","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"Why"},"572":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-2","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"573":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-3","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"574":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-4","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#where-you-see-it","content":"Where you see it"},"575":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-5","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#decision","content":"Conflicting statements resolve by supersession — a status flip, a `Supersedes` edge, bi-temporal stamps — with alternate phrasings kept as `Rephrase` edges and ambiguous conflicts adjudicated by an LLM on the background tick; Wikipedia-style revision machinery was evaluated and not built."},"576":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-6","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"The supersede chain is already a minimal history: nothing erased, both temporal clocks stamped, walkable via `as_of` / `include_history` — append-only revisions without a second storage mechanism."},"577":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-7","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"Fails open to coexistence: a hedged or unparseable verdict keeps both claims standing. A wrongful supersede silently hides a true claim; when in doubt, keep both."},"578":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-8","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"Kind gates the verdict: only a same-kind near-duplicate may supersede — a distilled `Claim` can never invalidate a user-asserted `Fact`. A two-level static rule, not a reputation system."},"579":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-9","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"Adjudication runs on the background tick — not at query time, not synchronously at ingest."},"580":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-10","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#why","content":"Example: \"deadline is March\" from ticket T-42; a month later the ticket says April. April supersedes March, closes its validity window, links the two. A query today returns April; `as_of` January returns March; `include_history` returns both, labelled."},"581":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-11","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"582":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-12","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"583":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-13","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"Full Wikipedia model (revision vectors, reputation, three-revert rule, protected thoughts)"},"584":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-14","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"solves a threat kern doesn't have — its editors are anonymous adversaries, kern's writers are cooperating agents; four coupled mechanisms against zero observed incidents"},"585":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-15","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"Bare supersede, no history"},"586":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-16","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#rejected","content":"no record of why a statement changed, no \"what did we believe last month\", no convergence story for ping-ponging producers"},"587":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-17","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#trade-off-accepted","content":"No edit rationale — a `Rephrase` edge carries the wording, not why; no edit-summary text."},"588":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-18","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#trade-off-accepted","content":"No revert rate-limit — supersede is asymmetric (ping-pong leaves a growing, visible chain), but nothing bounds it while it happens."},"589":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-19","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#trade-off-accepted","content":"Minimal history, not archival — a cold superseded revision is evicted to the capped cold tier and the temporal side-map does not follow; kern is a memory, not an encyclopedia."},"590":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-20","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#trade-off-accepted","content":"Deferred until triggers fire (none has): chains past \\~5 hops, producers ping-ponging a source, byte-level blame."},"591":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-21","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#where-you-see-it","content":"Queries return the current claim; `as_of` returns what was believed then; `include_history` returns the labelled chain."},"592":{"id":"/decisions/edit-convergence-22","page_id":"/decisions/edit-convergence","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/edit-convergence#where-you-see-it","content":"See Time & contradiction and Acceptance & routing."},"593":{"id":"/decisions","page_id":"/decisions","type":"page","content":"Design decisions","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions"},"594":{"id":"/decisions-0","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"One page per non-obvious mechanism: what was decided, why, what lost, what we knowingly gave up — current behaviour lives in Concepts."},"595":{"id":"/decisions-1","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Decision"},"596":{"id":"/decisions-2","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"In one sentence"},"597":{"id":"/decisions-3","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Stigmergy over gardening"},"598":{"id":"/decisions-4","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Forgetting is driven by a decaying heat scalar deposited by use, not by retention policies or manual curation."},"599":{"id":"/decisions-5","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"PageRank for authority"},"600":{"id":"/decisions-6","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Retrieval runs a damped, query-personalised PageRank over the reason graph and fuses it by rank."},"601":{"id":"/decisions-7","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Bayesian confidence"},"602":{"id":"/decisions-8","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Belief in a claim is a Beta distribution updated by weighted observations, not a scalar the last writer overwrites."},"603":{"id":"/decisions-9","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Edit convergence"},"604":{"id":"/decisions-10","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Conflicting statements resolve by supersession chains, not Wikipedia-style revision machinery."},"605":{"id":"/decisions-11","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"CRDTs over consensus"},"606":{"id":"/decisions-12","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Replicas converge through commutative per-field merges — no leader, no locks."},"607":{"id":"/decisions-13","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Knowledge, not gradients"},"608":{"id":"/decisions-14","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Peers gossip typed claims, never model updates; only federated learning's robustness tricks were kept."},"609":{"id":"/decisions-15","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"DiskANN-style spill"},"610":{"id":"/decisions-16","page_id":"/decisions","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions","content":"Past a size threshold the vector index spills to a memory-mapped Vamana snapshot; opt-in, not default."},"611":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","type":"page","content":"Knowledge, not gradients","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients"},"612":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-0","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#decision","content":"Decision"},"613":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-1","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"Why"},"614":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-2","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"615":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-3","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"616":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-4","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#decision","content":"kern federates knowledge artifacts — entities, reason edges, pulses — never model updates; from federated learning it borrows only robustness machinery, of which update clipping is the piece in code today."},"617":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-5","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"FL is the nearest well-studied relative, but the analogy breaks in three places:"},"618":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-6","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"The delta is the payload — an FL gradient is a lossy summary of private data; a kern gossip message *is* the thought. No summary layer to add noise to; privacy lives at scope and membership."},"619":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-7","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"No shared loss function — each node answers its own queries; \"convergence\" means eventual consistency over graph state, not loss minimisation."},"620":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-8","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"Time is not rounds — kern is a continuous Lamport-ordered stream; anything indexed by round number means nothing here."},"621":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-9","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"What shipped (all bounding what one peer can do to you):"},"622":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-10","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"Delta clamp (the FL-clipping translation): inbound counter deltas rejected if zero, malformed, or above 1,000,000 — a peer can lie within the bound, not overflow a counter in one message."},"623":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-11","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"Signals stripped at the boundary: synced entities arrive with heat, access counts, and confidence zeroed; confidence never merged. A remote assertion can make a fact *visible*, not *believed* or *hot*."},"624":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-12","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#why","content":"Remote quarantine: inbound entities land in a phantom `remote-*` kern, capped at 50,000 entities, never in your own."},"625":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-13","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"626":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-14","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"627":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-15","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"A coordinator"},"628":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-16","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"single point of failure; gossip + CRDTs + local scoring converge without one"},"629":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-17","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"DP noise on content"},"630":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-18","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"gradients tolerate noise because they're redundant; a thought is specific — noise destroys retrieval"},"631":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-19","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Cross-peer vector averaging"},"632":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-20","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"ids are content hashes: same-id vectors identical (no-op), different-model vectors meaningless arithmetic"},"633":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-21","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Shared model architecture"},"634":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-22","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"nodes are deliberately heterogeneous; local GNN weights excluded from federation"},"635":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-23","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Synchronous rounds"},"636":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-24","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"rounds need someone to fire them — the coordinator problem again"},"637":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-25","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"Gradient compression"},"638":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-26","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#rejected","content":"kern's deltas are a counter slot and a stamp; nothing to compress"},"639":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-27","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Adopted on paper, not built:"},"640":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-28","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Per-peer ingest budgets — the quarantine cap is the only volume bound, per remote kern, not per peer."},"641":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-29","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trimmed-mean materialisation of federated scalars — written once, never called, deleted."},"642":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-30","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Provenance ledger for retrospective down-weighting — the shipped ledger is a routing cache (where to fetch, not who told you what)."},"643":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-31","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Secure aggregation for pulses."},"644":{"id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients-32","page_id":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/knowledge-not-gradients#trade-off-accepted","content":"Every rejected primitive serves FL's goal of jointly training one model.\nkern's goal is that a fact learned once is available everywhere you work,\neach node deciding for itself what to believe. Import the wrong primitive\nand you quietly import the wrong goal."},"645":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"page","content":"PageRank for authority","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority"},"646":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-0","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#decision","content":"Decision"},"647":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-1","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Why"},"648":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-2","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"649":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-3","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"650":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-4","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#where-you-see-it","content":"Where you see it"},"651":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-5","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#decision","content":"Every query runs a damped, query-personalised PageRank over the reason graph (damping `0.85`, up to 25 iterations, teleporting at the query's seed hits) and fuses the top results into the seed set by rank (RRF); on by default."},"652":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-6","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Vector similarity cannot see the well-cited hub whose own text doesn't match the query; the graph knows which entities are load-bearing."},"653":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-7","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Personalisation: the walk restarts at the query's dense and lexical seeds, so rank mass stays in the query's neighbourhood; dangling mass redistributes along the teleport vector, not uniformly, or personalisation leaks back into a global prior."},"654":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-8","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Damping `d = 0.85` → expected walk `1/(1−d) ≈ 6.7` hops — long enough to see structure, short enough that a mutual-citation chain cannot launder rank down its length; self-loops neutral by construction."},"655":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-9","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Fusion consumes ranks only, never raw PageRank masses — no score-magnitude knob to mis-calibrate."},"656":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-10","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#why","content":"Net: structure decides *within* the neighbourhood the query selects, never *instead of* it."},"657":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-11","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"658":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-12","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"659":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-13","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Degree centrality"},"660":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-14","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"N fake citers buy N rank; no transitivity"},"661":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-15","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Undamped eigenvector centrality"},"662":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-16","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"diverges on dangling nodes; no convergence guarantee on disconnected components"},"663":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-17","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"HITS / SALSA"},"664":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-18","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"a second eigenvector to maintain; bipartite framing fits query/doc graphs, not a reason graph"},"665":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-19","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"TrustRank"},"666":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-20","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"right Sybil defence for federation-level authority — a scope that is unbuilt"},"667":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-21","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"Global (unpersonalised) PageRank"},"668":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-22","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#rejected","content":"popular entities top every query, relevant or not"},"669":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-23","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#trade-off-accepted","content":"A power iteration per query, nothing persisted between queries — and nothing *can* be, because the teleport is personalised: a per-graph vector would be the global PageRank rejected above. The walk is confined to the seeds' reach, so it costs what the query touches, not what the graph holds; a query whose seeds reach the whole graph still pays for the whole graph. No incremental updates."},"670":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-24","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#trade-off-accepted","content":"The federation half (per-peer authority, TrustRank seeding, Sybil defences) was not built; no rank crosses a machine boundary, so the targeted Sybil surface doesn't exist yet. Prerequisites if per-peer authority ever lands."},"671":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-25","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#trade-off-accepted","content":"The mechanism is pinned by unit tests, but an end-to-end test that adds a\nreason edge between two ingested claims moves only one of 8 pairs by one\nrank. Graph structure currently decides very little of the delivered ranking;\nROADMAP item 86 carries the diagnosis."},"672":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-26","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#where-you-see-it","content":"Within a query's neighbourhood, entities many reasons point at outrank textually-similar leaves."},"673":{"id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority-27","page_id":"/decisions/pagerank-authority","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/pagerank-authority#where-you-see-it","content":"Pipeline position (after seeding, before expansion): The retrieval pipeline. Peer trust today: Federation."},"674":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"page","content":"Stigmergy over gardening","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Decisions"],"tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening"},"675":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-0","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#decision","content":"Decision"},"676":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-1","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Why"},"677":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-2","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Rejected"},"678":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-3","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"Trade-off accepted"},"679":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-4","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#where-you-see-it","content":"Where you see it"},"680":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-5","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#decision","content":"Forgetting is driven by a decaying `heat` scalar deposited by use — reads deposit, an hourly collector evicts what goes cold — with no retention policies, quotas, or manual curation."},"681":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-6","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Three knobs total: deposit magnitude, evaporation rate, threshold floor. Everything else emergent."},"682":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-7","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Policy knobs multiply — every administered rule (\"but keep facts\") is another interacting special case."},"683":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-8","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Retention becomes a consequence of use, not a policy someone maintains."},"684":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-9","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Shipped constants:"},"685":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-10","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Read deposits `1.0` heat, off the query hot path. It is the only deposit."},"686":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-11","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Decay is lazy, from last-deposit age; half-life is preset-owned (`relaxed` 30 days by default); a deposit decays the stale value first, never resurrecting old magnitude."},"687":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-12","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Hourly GC demotes entities that are cold (aged heat below `0.01`), stale (untouched 7 days), and not durable — spilled to the cold tier, not deleted."},"688":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-13","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#why","content":"Net: one read survives 6.64 half-lives — \\~**199 days** on `relaxed`, \\~46 on `medium`, \\~20 on `tight`; repeat reads never decay past half peak."},"689":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-14","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Alternative"},"690":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-15","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Why it lost"},"691":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-16","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"TTLs"},"692":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-17","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"delete the fact you needed on day 31"},"693":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-18","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"LRU / quotas"},"694":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-19","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"evict by an ordering (insertion, size, age) unrelated to usefulness"},"695":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-20","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Manual gardening"},"696":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-21","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"doesn't scale past one attentive operator; silently stops happening"},"697":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-22","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Per-edge pheromone"},"698":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-23","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"storage cost for a weak signal; traversal counts feed scoring, not retention"},"699":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-24","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Multiple pheromone types"},"700":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-25","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"one scalar suffices; entity kinds already provide orthogonal typing"},"701":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-26","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"Cross-peer heat gossip"},"702":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-27","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#rejected","content":"a peer's usage is not evidence of yours; an injection surface"},"703":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-28","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"Heat is retention-only; ranking keeps its own two-term freshness boost with a 24-hour half-life — two freshness signals, by design not unification."},"704":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-29","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"The half-life errs heavily toward retention (6.64 half-lives per read, not one, because the cold gate is `0.01` and not half peak)."},"705":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-30","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"Convergence metrics never built — the access-distribution claim is design intent, not measurement."},"706":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-31","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"The pulse used to deposit too, and a recurring deposit of *any* size settles far above the `0.01` gate: everything within its 5-level reach was permanently exempt from collection, used or not. Removed — retention is a consequence of use only (`tests/depth_bias.rs`)."},"707":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-32","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#trade-off-accepted","content":"Active `Fact` and `Document` entities are immune to collection (locally — peers\ncannot pin storage by labelling gossip `kind=Fact`). Supersession revokes the\nimmunity. See Heat & compaction."},"708":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-33","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#where-you-see-it","content":"Unused memories quietly demote to the cold tier once heat clears the floor — months on `relaxed`, weeks on `tight`; anything you recall stays hot."},"709":{"id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening-34","page_id":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/decisions/stigmergy-over-gardening#where-you-see-it","content":"Details: Stigmergy GC & gravitons, Heat, decay & self-compaction."},"710":{"id":"/howto/configure","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"page","content":"Configure models","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure"},"711":{"id":"/howto/configure-0","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#you-may-not-need-a-config-file","content":"You may not need a config file"},"712":{"id":"/howto/configure-1","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"Presets — the whole tuning surface is one line"},"713":{"id":"/howto/configure-2","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#hold-auto-distilled-claims-until-someone-reviews-them","content":"Hold auto-distilled claims until someone reviews them"},"714":{"id":"/howto/configure-3","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#the-two-model-roles","content":"The two model roles"},"715":{"id":"/howto/configure-4","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#embed","content":"`embed`"},"716":{"id":"/howto/configure-5","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#reason","content":"`reason`"},"717":{"id":"/howto/configure-6","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#there-is-no-answer-role","content":"There is no answer role"},"718":{"id":"/howto/configure-7","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Where the config file lives"},"719":{"id":"/howto/configure-8","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#a-complete-ollama-config","content":"A complete Ollama config"},"720":{"id":"/howto/configure-9","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"OpenAI-compatible and remote endpoints"},"721":{"id":"/howto/configure-10","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"Verify"},"722":{"id":"/howto/configure-11","page_id":"/howto/configure","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/configure#related","content":"Related"},"723":{"id":"/howto/configure-12","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure","content":"kern talks to two model endpoints. With a local Ollama and the default models pulled, no config is needed."},"724":{"id":"/howto/configure-13","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#you-may-not-need-a-config-file","content":"No `kern.toml`: defaults assume a local Ollama at `http://localhost:11434`:"},"725":{"id":"/howto/configure-14","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#you-may-not-need-a-config-file","content":"A config file only overrides; omitted sections keep their defaults."},"726":{"id":"/howto/configure-15","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"The preset owns every heat, dedup, and retrieval-breadth setting. `[heat]`, `[ingest]`, `[retrieval]` sections are not accepted — a config that sets them refuses to load. The one exception is `[ingest] review_policy` below, which is curation rather than tuning. Unknown preset name: refuses to load."},"727":{"id":"/howto/configure-16","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"Preset"},"728":{"id":"/howto/configure-17","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"Posture"},"729":{"id":"/howto/configure-18","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"What it means"},"730":{"id":"/howto/configure-19","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"`relaxed`"},"731":{"id":"/howto/configure-20","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"**The default.** Keep more, forget slower"},"732":{"id":"/howto/configure-21","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"30-day heat half-life, near-identical-only dedup (0.98), broad search (`seed_k` 25, 800 expansions), up to 40 results"},"733":{"id":"/howto/configure-22","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"`medium`"},"734":{"id":"/howto/configure-23","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"Balanced"},"735":{"id":"/howto/configure-24","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"7-day half-life, 0.95 dedup, `seed_k` 15, 500 expansions, 25 results"},"736":{"id":"/howto/configure-25","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"`tight`"},"737":{"id":"/howto/configure-26","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"Lean graph, sharp recall"},"738":{"id":"/howto/configure-27","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"3-day half-life, aggressive dedup (0.90), narrow search (`seed_k` 10, 250 expansions), 12 results"},"739":{"id":"/howto/configure-28","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#presets--the-whole-tuning-surface-is-one-line","content":"`relaxed` when losing a stray fact hurts more than noise; `tight` for high-churn codebases where stale memory misleads."},"740":{"id":"/howto/configure-29","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#hold-auto-distilled-claims-until-someone-reviews-them","content":"`review_policy` keys a curation state on the source scheme — `file`, `ticket`, `session`, `agent`, `inline`. A scheme set to `pending` arrives held; a scheme you do not name arrives `active`, which is every ingest path today."},"741":{"id":"/howto/configure-30","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#hold-auto-distilled-claims-until-someone-reviews-them","content":"Holding a claim does not hide it. `kern query` still returns it, because a filter that can hide data must be asked for:"},"742":{"id":"/howto/configure-31","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#hold-auto-distilled-claims-until-someone-reviews-them","content":"A misspelled scheme refuses to load rather than holding nothing and reading as a working knob. `kern promote` is idempotent — releasing an already-active thought reports it and changes nothing."},"743":{"id":"/howto/configure-32","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#hold-auto-distilled-claims-until-someone-reviews-them","content":"`kern promote` routes to a running daemon over its local socket. The socket is owner-only (`0600`) and authenticated with the graph's `mcp-token`; any caller holding that token can release a held claim. kern has no finer-grained caller identity — the process boundary is the access model."},"744":{"id":"/howto/configure-33","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#embed","content":"Critical path for every ingest and query — the highest-frequency call. Keep it small; default `qwen3-embedding:0.6b` is fine. `embed.url` and `embed.model` are the only required settings — validation rejects a config with either blank."},"745":{"id":"/howto/configure-34","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#embed","content":"First ingest fixes the vector dimension for the whole graph. Change the model later and stored vectors no longer match query vectors. Not silent — store stamps its model, `health` raises `embed_mismatch`, wrong-dimension query vectors are dropped and counted. Queries still answer — badly. `kern reembed` is the only escape; it re-embeds everything and restamps."},"746":{"id":"/howto/configure-35","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#reason","content":"Critical path for the intake: one distillation pass per drained session decides what is remembered — an unextracted claim never enters the graph. Also used for contradiction classification and `link` reasons. Default `granite4:3b`, sized for a small GPU. **Spend headroom here first** — off the read path, so a slower model costs ingest latency, not recall latency."},"747":{"id":"/howto/configure-36","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#there-is-no-answer-role","content":"`query` returns scored passages; the calling agent synthesizes. A config carrying an `[answer]` section refuses to load."},"748":{"id":"/howto/configure-37","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Both optional:"},"749":{"id":"/howto/configure-38","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Scope"},"750":{"id":"/howto/configure-39","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Path"},"751":{"id":"/howto/configure-40","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Project"},"752":{"id":"/howto/configure-41","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"`<project root>/.kern/kern.toml`"},"753":{"id":"/howto/configure-42","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"User"},"754":{"id":"/howto/configure-43","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"`<XDG_CONFIG>/kern/kern.toml`"},"755":{"id":"/howto/configure-44","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Project root: nearest ancestor with `.git`, else nearest with `.kern` — subdirectory launches find the same config."},"756":{"id":"/howto/configure-45","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Scopes deep-merge: project key overrides user key, omitted keys inherited; arrays and scalars replace wholesale. Exception: &#x2A;*a scope that sets a section's `url` does not inherit that section's `key`** — otherwise a cloned repo's config could point `[embed] url` at its own endpoint and harvest your global credential. Redirect an endpoint → supply its key or go without."},"757":{"id":"/howto/configure-46","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"Invalid config aborts startup: offending key on stderr, exit **78** (`EX_CONFIG`). Absent config defaults silently."},"758":{"id":"/howto/configure-47","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#where-the-config-file-lives","content":"No environment-variable layer; API keys live in plaintext in the TOML — treat the file accordingly."},"759":{"id":"/howto/configure-48","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#a-complete-ollama-config","content":"Every line is a default made explicit — delete any you are not changing:"},"760":{"id":"/howto/configure-49","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#a-complete-ollama-config","content":"Blank = \"same as the leg above\": `reason.url` blank → `embed.url`; `reason.key` blank → `embed.key`. One endpoint for both models: write the URL once, in `[embed]`."},"761":{"id":"/howto/configure-50","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#a-complete-ollama-config","content":"WSL2 NAT with Ollama on the Windows host: `localhost` resolves inside the VM. Set `embed.url` to the host gateway (`ip route show default | awk '{print $3}'`). Mirrored-mode WSL2 and in-distro Ollama keep plain `localhost`."},"762":{"id":"/howto/configure-51","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"Protocol is picked from the URL: Ollama-native (`/api/embed`, `/api/chat`) only when the URL looks local *and* does not end in `/v1`; anything else gets the OpenAI-compatible API (`/v1/embeddings`, `/v1/chat/completions`) with `key` as bearer token. A trailing `/v1` is stripped before building the request path — writing it is what selects the protocol."},"763":{"id":"/howto/configure-52","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"**Hosted OpenAI-compatible provider:**"},"764":{"id":"/howto/configure-53","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"**Local OpenAI-compatible server** (vLLM, llama.cpp, LM Studio) — `/v1` **required**, else a `localhost` URL is treated as Ollama-native and requests go to `/api/chat`, which your server does not serve:"},"765":{"id":"/howto/configure-54","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"**Remote Ollama** on a non-local host: always driven OpenAI-compatible — point at `http://host:11434/v1` and be explicit."},"766":{"id":"/howto/configure-55","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#openai-compatible-and-remote-endpoints","content":"`num_ctx` (embed 2048, reason 8192) and `keep_alive` (embed 10m, reason 2m) are compiled-in constants, Ollama-native only. On the `/v1` path kern sends none of them."},"767":{"id":"/howto/configure-56","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"Restart the daemon, then:"},"768":{"id":"/howto/configure-57","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"Reason leg is write-path only — drop a delta into `.kern/intake/` and watch it drain (Intake & recall)."},"769":{"id":"/howto/configure-58","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"`--embed-url`, `--embed-model`, `--reason-url`, `--reason-model` override config for a single command — test an endpoint before committing it."},"770":{"id":"/howto/configure-59","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"Embedding failure: ingest and query return nothing rather than erroring (fail open) — check stderr for the connection error."},"771":{"id":"/howto/configure-60","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#verify","content":"Mismatch is visible: `kern health` prints `MISMATCH: the index was built with a different model` beside `embed:`; fix with `kern reembed`. An unstamped store (pre-stamping build) adopts the current model on first open — not a mismatch."},"772":{"id":"/howto/configure-61","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#related","content":"Install & run"},"773":{"id":"/howto/configure-62","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#related","content":"Seed the graph"},"774":{"id":"/howto/configure-63","page_id":"/howto/configure","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/configure#related","content":"The retrieval pipeline"},"775":{"id":"/howto/hub","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"page","content":"The hub","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub"},"776":{"id":"/howto/hub-0","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"What it does"},"777":{"id":"/howto/hub-1","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"Auto-start and auto-restart"},"778":{"id":"/howto/hub-2","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#idle-unload","content":"Idle unload"},"779":{"id":"/howto/hub-3","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#where-state-lives","content":"Where state lives"},"780":{"id":"/howto/hub-4","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#commands","content":"Commands"},"781":{"id":"/howto/hub-5","page_id":"/howto/hub","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/hub#next","content":"Next"},"782":{"id":"/howto/hub-6","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub","content":"A machine-level supervisor that owns detached kern daemons. It is not a server\nof graphs — each daemon still owns its own per-cwd graph and socket — it is the\none process a host runs to spawn, find, unload, and stop them."},"783":{"id":"/howto/hub-7","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"**Resolve** a cwd to the daemon serving it (or spawns one and reports the\nsocket path), so `kern mcp` and other clients never have to race the bind\nthemselves."},"784":{"id":"/howto/hub-8","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"**Status** — every hub-owned daemon, alive or parked, with its pid and idle\ntime."},"785":{"id":"/howto/hub-9","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"**Unload** an idle hub-owned daemon from memory without stopping the hub."},"786":{"id":"/howto/hub-10","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"**Merge** — `kern hub merge <src> <dst>` performs an offline CRDT union of\n`src`'s graph into `dst`'s. **Both daemons are stopped first**; `src` is read\nonly and never written. Use it to consolidate a project's graph into another."},"787":{"id":"/howto/hub-11","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#what-it-does","content":"**Stop** — ends the hub daemon; **nodes stay up**. A node without a hub is\njust a daemon with a socket, still serving its graph."},"788":{"id":"/howto/hub-12","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`[hub]` config (`kern.toml`):"},"789":{"id":"/howto/hub-13","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"Key"},"790":{"id":"/howto/hub-14","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"Default"},"791":{"id":"/howto/hub-15","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"Effect"},"792":{"id":"/howto/hub-16","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`auto_start`"},"793":{"id":"/howto/hub-17","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`true`"},"794":{"id":"/howto/hub-18","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`kern mcp` spawn-attaches a detached hub when none answers, the same way it auto-spawns a project daemon. `false` = hub is opt-in via `kern hub`, and the direct-connect fallback still works."},"795":{"id":"/howto/hub-19","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`auto_restart`"},"796":{"id":"/howto/hub-20","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"`true`"},"797":{"id":"/howto/hub-21","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#auto-start-and-auto-restart","content":"A client attaching to a daemon built from a different binary, or booted against a different config, restarts that daemon before proxying. Without this a long-lived detached daemon serves stale code and stale config indefinitely — the failure that makes every shipped fix look like it did nothing."},"798":{"id":"/howto/hub-22","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#idle-unload","content":"A hub-owned daemon idle for `--idle-unload-secs` (default **1800 s** = 30 min) is\nunloaded and re-spawned on next contact; `0` disables. The root daemon is never\nauto-unloaded. Idle time is stamped in the MCP dispatch core and every typed\nRPC method, and the reaper double-checks under the root lock — a node that\ntouched anything between the sweep scheduling and the sweep running stays."},"799":{"id":"/howto/hub-23","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#where-state-lives","content":"Hub socket: `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/kern-hub.sock` (or `/tmp/kern-hub-<user>.sock`\non Unix; `\\\\.\\pipe\\kern-hub-<user>` on Windows)."},"800":{"id":"/howto/hub-24","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#where-state-lives","content":"Node handles live next to the hub daemon's; the per-project graph still lives\nunder `<project>/.kern/data` — the hub never owns graph data."},"801":{"id":"/howto/hub-25","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#next","content":"Install & run"},"802":{"id":"/howto/hub-26","page_id":"/howto/hub","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/hub#next","content":"Wire up MCP"},"803":{"id":"/howto/install-run","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"page","content":"Install & run","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run"},"804":{"id":"/howto/install-run-0","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#prerequisites","content":"Prerequisites"},"805":{"id":"/howto/install-run-1","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#1-install","content":"1\\. Install"},"806":{"id":"/howto/install-run-2","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#2-opt-the-project-in","content":"2\\. Opt the project in"},"807":{"id":"/howto/install-run-3","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#3-start-the-daemon","content":"3\\. Start the daemon"},"808":{"id":"/howto/install-run-4","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"Where state lives"},"809":{"id":"/howto/install-run-5","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Is it healthy?"},"810":{"id":"/howto/install-run-6","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#stopping","content":"Stopping"},"811":{"id":"/howto/install-run-7","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#starting-over","content":"Starting over"},"812":{"id":"/howto/install-run-8","page_id":"/howto/install-run","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/install-run#next","content":"Next"},"813":{"id":"/howto/install-run-9","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run","content":"Binary on PATH, one daemon per project, graph under `.kern/`."},"814":{"id":"/howto/install-run-10","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#prerequisites","content":"Local Ollama with the default models:"},"815":{"id":"/howto/install-run-11","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#prerequisites","content":"No answer model — `query` returns scored passages; your agent synthesizes. Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint works: Configure models."},"816":{"id":"/howto/install-run-12","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#1-install","content":"From source: `cargo build --release` or `cargo install --path .`."},"817":{"id":"/howto/install-run-13","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#2-opt-the-project-in","content":"kern re-pins to the nearest ancestor with `.git` (else `.kern/`) — subdirectory launches attach to the project's graph."},"818":{"id":"/howto/install-run-14","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#3-start-the-daemon","content":"Usually unnecessary — `kern mcp` auto-spawns a detached daemon. See Wire up MCP."},"819":{"id":"/howto/install-run-15","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#3-start-the-daemon","content":"Invalid `kern.toml`: offending key on stderr, exit **78** (`EX_CONFIG`), every invocation. Absent config boots on defaults — deleting the file is a valid fix."},"820":{"id":"/howto/install-run-16","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"All under `<project>/.kern/`:"},"821":{"id":"/howto/install-run-17","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"Path"},"822":{"id":"/howto/install-run-18","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"What it is"},"823":{"id":"/howto/install-run-19","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/data/data.mdb`"},"824":{"id":"/howto/install-run-20","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"The LMDB environment: hot graph plus cold tier."},"825":{"id":"/howto/install-run-21","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/data/lock.mdb`"},"826":{"id":"/howto/install-run-22","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"LMDB's lock file. Never edit or delete while running."},"827":{"id":"/howto/install-run-23","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/intake/*`"},"828":{"id":"/howto/install-run-24","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"Dropped files waiting to drain: `.txt` distilled as transcripts, anything else stored as documents."},"829":{"id":"/howto/install-run-25","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/kern.toml`"},"830":{"id":"/howto/install-run-26","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"Optional config overrides. Absent by default."},"831":{"id":"/howto/install-run-27","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/data/mcp-token`"},"832":{"id":"/howto/install-run-28","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"Bearer token for the HTTP surface, minted on first use."},"833":{"id":"/howto/install-run-29","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"`.kern/data/logs/*.log`"},"834":{"id":"/howto/install-run-30","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"stdout+stderr of detached children (`daemon.log`, `hub.log`). Owner-only, append-only."},"835":{"id":"/howto/install-run-31","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#where-state-lives","content":"RPC socket, outside the project: `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/kern-<tag>.sock` (or `/tmp/kern-<user>-<tag>.sock`) on Unix; named pipe `\\\\.\\pipe\\kern-<user>-<tag>` on Windows. `<tag>` = hash of the canonical cwd — one daemon and graph per project. A second `kern --daemon` in the same directory loses the bind race:"},"836":{"id":"/howto/install-run-32","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"`kern health` or the `health` MCP tool:"},"837":{"id":"/howto/install-run-33","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Non-zero entities: graph has content."},"838":{"id":"/howto/install-run-34","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Growing `unnamed`: clustering has work queued."},"839":{"id":"/howto/install-run-35","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Non-zero panics/failures: maintenance degraded but still running."},"840":{"id":"/howto/install-run-36","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Climbing `cold_evicted`: 50k cold cap dropping old thoughts for good."},"841":{"id":"/howto/install-run-37","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"`MISMATCH` on the `embed:` line: index built with a different model — `kern reembed`."},"842":{"id":"/howto/install-run-38","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"No daemon: prints `tick: (no daemon serving this directory)` instead of blocking."},"843":{"id":"/howto/install-run-39","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"`.kern/intake/` should drain, not accumulate — `kern intake` names anything `STUCK` and why (usually a missing `[reason]` model). Nothing lost; deltas stay queued, and `kern intake drain` forces a pass — through the daemon when one is serving, in-process when none is."},"844":{"id":"/howto/install-run-40","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"Logs: stderr, default level `warn`. Detached children append to `.kern/data/logs/daemon.log` / `hub.log` — never truncated."},"845":{"id":"/howto/install-run-41","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"`kern status` answers who is serving and who is writing:"},"846":{"id":"/howto/install-run-42","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#is-it-healthy","content":"The `kern <subcommand>` CLI opens the graph directly, so it can race a live daemon — use MCP tools for live state. The offline admin commands (`kern reembed`, `kern compact`, `kern gc`) now take the writer lock and **refuse** while a daemon holds it, naming the holder, rather than losing a rewrite to whichever process flushes last. The lock is released by the OS when its holder exits, kill included, so a crash never leaves a stale one to clean up."},"847":{"id":"/howto/install-run-43","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#stopping","content":"Ctrl-C in the foreground, or `pkill -f 'kern --daemon'`. Runs a final flush, prints `shutting down...` then `done` — `SIGKILL` mid-flush drops whatever was only in RAM."},"848":{"id":"/howto/install-run-44","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#starting-over","content":"Daemon stopped:"},"849":{"id":"/howto/install-run-45","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#starting-over","content":"`data.mdb` shrinks only on compaction — next restart auto-compacts, or `kern compact` offline."},"850":{"id":"/howto/install-run-46","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#starting-over","content":"Alpha: store format changes are not migrated — an old `data.mdb` is rejected; wipe `.kern/data` and reingest."},"851":{"id":"/howto/install-run-47","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#next","content":"Wire up MCP"},"852":{"id":"/howto/install-run-48","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#next","content":"Intake & recall"},"853":{"id":"/howto/install-run-49","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#next","content":"Seed the graph"},"854":{"id":"/howto/install-run-50","page_id":"/howto/install-run","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/install-run#next","content":"Architecture"},"855":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"page","content":"Intake & recall","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall"},"856":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-0","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#before-you-start","content":"Before you start"},"857":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-1","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#1-opt-the-project-in","content":"1\\. Opt the project in"},"858":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-2","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#2-start-the-daemon","content":"2\\. Start the daemon"},"859":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-3","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"3\\. Seed gravitons and claim kinds"},"860":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-4","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"4\\. Drop a session into the intake"},"861":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-5","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#5-recall-in-the-next-session","content":"5\\. Recall in the next session"},"862":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-6","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"What a healthy graph looks like"},"863":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-7","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"When it does not work"},"864":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-8","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/intake-recall#tuning","content":"Tuning"},"865":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-9","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall","content":"Start a daemon, seed the graph, drop an intake delta, confirm it landed."},"866":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-10","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#before-you-start","content":"`kern` on PATH, local Ollama with both default models:"},"867":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-11","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#before-you-start","content":"Embedding dimension locks into the graph on first ingest; switching models later requires `kern reembed`. Not silent: store stamps its model, `kern health` prints `MISMATCH` beside `embed:`, wrong-dimension query vectors are dropped and counted."},"868":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-12","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#1-opt-the-project-in","content":"Pins to the nearest ancestor with `.git` or `.kern`. No config file required — create `.kern/kern.toml` only to override a default."},"869":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-13","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#2-start-the-daemon","content":"Let your MCP client start it — `kern mcp` attaches to a running daemon, auto-spawns a detached one if none answers:"},"870":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-14","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#2-start-the-daemon","content":"The daemon writes this entry into `.mcp.json` on startup if absent. To watch the first run (logs on stderr only; stdout is reserved for JSON-RPC):"},"871":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-15","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"Once per project, via MCP against the running daemon (the CLI can race a live daemon)."},"872":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-16","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"`graviton` tool, `action: \"add\"` per focus area — e.g. *decisions*, *project state*, *preferences*."},"873":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-17","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"Seed `text`: **example statements, one per line** — each line embedded separately, mean-pooled into the pull vector; routes far better than an abstract description."},"874":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-18","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"Optional `mass` (default `1.0`): stronger attraction."},"875":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-19","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"Unmatched claims → `generic`. See Acceptance & routing."},"876":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-20","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"Built-in claim kinds: `preference`, `decision`, `project`, `fact`, `code-fact`, `reference`, `procedural`. Extras via `claim_kind`; registered kinds are offered to the distillation LLM alongside built-ins."},"877":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-21","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#3-seed-gravitons-and-claim-kinds","content":"CLI equivalents, daemon stopped:"},"878":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-22","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"Anything writing a `.txt` delta into `.kern/intake/` feeds kern — client hook, shell wrapper, your own script:"},"879":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-23","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"Daemon polls every 5s, distills each delta in one LLM pass, ingests the typed claims."},"880":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-24","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"Moves to `.kern/intake/done/` only once every claim committed; LLM outage → stays put, retried."},"881":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-25","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"Archived deltas pruned after seven days."},"882":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-26","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#4-drop-a-session-into-the-intake","content":"Synchronous, already-typed ingest (skips distillation): `ingest` MCP tool or `kern ingest`."},"883":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-27","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#5-recall-in-the-next-session","content":"`query` MCP tool: `mode`, `kind`, `source`, time ranges, `min_conf`, `as_of` (point-in-time), `include_history` (supersede chains). Returns scored passages, edges, chains — the agent synthesizes. See Retrieval."},"884":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-28","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#5-recall-in-the-next-session","content":"Shell: `kern search \"indentation\" --k 5` or `kern query \"what did we decide about indentation\"`."},"885":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-29","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"`reasons` well above `thoughts` — claims connecting, not just arriving."},"886":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-30","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"`gravitons` non-empty — `(none)` means seeding never happened; everything piles into `generic`."},"887":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-31","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"`unnamed` small relative to `thoughts` — large share means gravitons don't cover the content."},"888":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-32","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"`done/` filling while `.kern/intake/` stays near empty — drain keeping pace."},"889":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-33","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#what-a-healthy-graph-looks-like","content":"Non-zero panics/failures — something dying; the line beneath names the task."},"890":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-34","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"Start with `kern intake`. A queued delta is retried forever rather than dropped, so a permanently stuck one looks exactly like a fresh one until you ask:"},"891":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-35","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"`STUCK` carries the last failure and is the whole diagnosis; `wait` means not picked up yet. `kern intake drain` forces one pass — routed to the daemon when one is serving so it never drains twice, in this process when none is — so you can drive the queue with no daemon at all and read the error immediately."},"892":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-36","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"**LLM endpoint unreachable.** Transient: deltas queue and retry forever. `kern intake` shows them `STUCK` with the reason; confirm with `curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags`. WSL (NAT) with Ollama on the Windows host: `localhost` resolves inside the VM — pin the URL to the host gateway (`ip route show default | awk '{print $3}'`) in `.kern/kern.toml`. Blanking both `[reason].url` and `[embed].url` disables distillation; the daemon logs a warning."},"893":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-37","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"**Nothing landing.** Check in order: `.kern/` exists where the daemon pinned; `[intake].enabled` is `true`; something is writing files. Non-UTF-8 → `.kern/intake/failed/`. Endpoint answers but drain never finishes: prose-not-JSON — `kern intake` names it."},"894":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-38","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#when-it-does-not-work","content":"**Recall empty.** `kern health` shows content: check `MISMATCH` beside `embed:` (fix: `kern reembed`). Otherwise widen the query — `min_conf` gates out fresh claims, which start at 0.6 until reinforced."},"895":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-39","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#tuning","content":"`poll_secs = 0` rejected by the validator (busy-loop)."},"896":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-40","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#tuning","content":"`retention_secs` is the standing per-source policy behind `kern ingest --retention-secs`: \"everything dropped in this queue expires in 30 days\"\n(`2592000`), said once instead of per call. It becomes a `valid_until` on the\nentity — distinct from `done_retention_secs`, which prunes the archived *files*\nin `done/`. The file watcher has the same key for the same reason:"},"897":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-41","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#tuning","content":"Both live here rather than in `[ingest]` because that section is preset-owned\nand a user `kern.toml` is refused for setting it."},"898":{"id":"/howto/intake-recall-42","page_id":"/howto/intake-recall","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/intake-recall#tuning","content":"Related: Acceptance & routing · Configure · MCP"},"899":{"id":"/howto/mcp","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"page","content":"Wire up MCP","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp"},"900":{"id":"/howto/mcp-0","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#1-register-the-server","content":"1\\. Register the server"},"901":{"id":"/howto/mcp-1","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#2-what-kern-mcp-does","content":"2\\. What `kern mcp` does"},"902":{"id":"/howto/mcp-2","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#3-the-tools","content":"3\\. The tools"},"903":{"id":"/howto/mcp-3","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#reading","content":"Reading"},"904":{"id":"/howto/mcp-4","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"Writing"},"905":{"id":"/howto/mcp-5","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"Shaping and maintenance"},"906":{"id":"/howto/mcp-6","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#4-verify","content":"4\\. Verify"},"907":{"id":"/howto/mcp-7","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"5\\. Zero tools in the client"},"908":{"id":"/howto/mcp-8","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#mcp-over-http","content":"MCP over HTTP"},"909":{"id":"/howto/mcp-9","page_id":"/howto/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/mcp#next","content":"Next"},"910":{"id":"/howto/mcp-10","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp","content":"Get your agent listing kern's fifteen tools against the project's graph. Start from a project with `.kern/` — see Install & run."},"911":{"id":"/howto/mcp-11","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#1-register-the-server","content":"stdio:"},"912":{"id":"/howto/mcp-12","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#1-register-the-server","content":"Daemon writes exactly this into `.mcp.json` on startup if the `kern` key is missing; a customised entry is never overwritten."},"913":{"id":"/howto/mcp-13","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#1-register-the-server","content":"Windows clients that won't search PATH: absolute path as `command` (`C:\\Users\\<you>\\.kern\\bin\\kern.exe` style)."},"914":{"id":"/howto/mcp-14","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#2-what-kern-mcp-does","content":"One config entry brings kern up — no separate daemon start needed."},"915":{"id":"/howto/mcp-15","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#2-what-kern-mcp-does","content":"Standalone fallback is a second writer against the same LMDB environment — a safety net, not a mode. Tools work but the graph never grows across sessions: you are falling back silently; start a daemon by hand and check the socket."},"916":{"id":"/howto/mcp-16","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#reading","content":"**`query`** — hybrid vector + lexical retrieval; scored thoughts with edges and path chains, no synthesis. Needs `text` or `id`. Filters: `kind` (`fact` / `document` / `normal`), `source`, `min_conf`; `since` / `before`, `sort` + `ascending`; `as_of` for what was believed at a past instant; `include_history: true` for superseded revisions (flagged `history: true`). Every filter applies to an `id` read too."},"917":{"id":"/howto/mcp-17","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#reading","content":"**`health`** — counts plus degradation: tick queue and latency, `task_panics` / `task_failures`, `cold_evicted`, `embed_model` / `embed_dim` with `embed_mismatch`. kern fails open — a degraded daemon keeps serving and shows up only here."},"918":{"id":"/howto/mcp-18","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`ingest`** — put text in. `object_id` = update semantics for revisions; `hint` folded into the chunking prompt; `conf` weights the claim; `sync: true` blocks until complete."},"919":{"id":"/howto/mcp-19","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`link`** — reason edge between two thoughts. Empty `reason`: the LLM writes the justification."},"920":{"id":"/howto/mcp-20","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`forget`** — remove a thought, cascade-delete its edges. Facts immune; rewrite history via superseding `ingest` with the same `object_id`."},"921":{"id":"/howto/mcp-21","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`forget_by_source`** — the host-deletion cascade: remove every thought ingested from one source, all its sections, edges cascaded. Keys on `scheme` + `object_id`. Local Facts are spared unless `force: true`; a remote Fact goes either way."},"922":{"id":"/howto/mcp-22","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`degrade`** — feedback. Bad result's id as `query_id`: edges along that path lose score."},"923":{"id":"/howto/mcp-23","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`move`** — relocate a thought to another kern (`id`, `to_kern`), edges carried."},"924":{"id":"/howto/mcp-24","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#writing","content":"**`promote`** — the release half of the review lifecycle: mark a thought reviewed, moving it from `pending` back to `active` so a `query` asking `exclude_pending` returns it again. Idempotent."},"925":{"id":"/howto/mcp-25","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`graviton`** — focus attractors. `add` with name and seed `text` (example statements, one per line — Seed the graph), optional `mass` (routing divides distance by mass); `list`, `remove`. Unmatched → `generic`."},"926":{"id":"/howto/mcp-26","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`claim_kind`** — `add` with a markdown `description`, or `rm`; extends the built-in set distillation may label with."},"927":{"id":"/howto/mcp-27","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`pulse`** — force a clustering pass now. Useful after a bulk seed."},"928":{"id":"/howto/mcp-28","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`setup`** — wiring instructions for the calling agent: seed gravitons, install the capture hook, verify with an ingest/health/query round-trip. Idempotent — reports what is already `[done]`. Once per new project or agent host."},"929":{"id":"/howto/mcp-29","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`gc`** — reap empty/orphan kerns live. Returns before/after counts and `data.mdb` size (may not drop — LMDB returns disk only on compaction: next restart or offline `kern compact`)."},"930":{"id":"/howto/mcp-30","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"**`intake_drain`** — drain `.kern/intake/` now rather than at the next poll: queued `.txt` transcripts distilled, other readable files ingested whole, whatever committed archived into `done/`. No arguments; returns `archived`. `kern intake drain` routes through this, so the CLI and the daemon never drain the same file twice."},"931":{"id":"/howto/mcp-31","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#shaping-and-maintenance","content":"Default loop: `query` to recall, `ingest` durable conclusions, `degrade` on a misfire; leave `pulse`/`gc` to the tick unless you just bulk-loaded."},"932":{"id":"/howto/mcp-32","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#4-verify","content":"List tools in your client — expect all fifteen. Or drive stdio:"},"933":{"id":"/howto/mcp-33","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#4-verify","content":"Confirm the graph answers, not just the transport:"},"934":{"id":"/howto/mcp-34","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#4-verify","content":"Non-zero `entities` = populated graph. Zero on a fresh project is expected — seed it."},"935":{"id":"/howto/mcp-35","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**`kern` on the client's PATH?** GUI clients often don't inherit shell PATH — use an absolute `command`."},"936":{"id":"/howto/mcp-36","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**stdout clean?** JSON-RPC rides stdout; logs go to stderr. A shell profile echoing on startup corrupts the stream."},"937":{"id":"/howto/mcp-37","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**Working directory right?** Daemon and socket are per-cwd; re-pins to the nearest ancestor with `.kern/` only if one exists above."},"938":{"id":"/howto/mcp-38","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**Stale socket?** Daemon died hard: remove `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/kern-*.sock`, let `kern mcp` respawn."},"939":{"id":"/howto/mcp-39","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**Config aborting the boot?** Invalid `kern.toml` exits **78** with the offending key on stderr — the client sees an immediately dying process. Deleting the file is a valid fix."},"940":{"id":"/howto/mcp-40","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"**Read the logs.** `RUST_LOG=kern=info kern mcp` prints proxy (\"attached to running daemon\") vs standalone (\"auto-spawn failed\"). Spawned daemon output appends to `.kern/data/logs/daemon.log`."},"941":{"id":"/howto/mcp-41","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#5-zero-tools-in-the-client","content":"In proxy mode, `resources/list` and `prompts/list` are not forwarded — `-32601 method not found`. The tools are the stable surface."},"942":{"id":"/howto/mcp-42","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#mcp-over-http","content":"MCP Streamable HTTP, never unauthenticated: bearer token read from — or minted into — `.kern/data/mcp-token` on first use. Send `Authorization: Bearer <token>`."},"943":{"id":"/howto/mcp-43","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#mcp-over-http","content":"Bind address from `--mcp-addr` only; `kern.toml` has no field for it."},"944":{"id":"/howto/mcp-44","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#next","content":"Configure models"},"945":{"id":"/howto/mcp-45","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#next","content":"Intake & recall"},"946":{"id":"/howto/mcp-46","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#next","content":"The retrieval pipeline"},"947":{"id":"/howto/mcp-47","page_id":"/howto/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/mcp#next","content":"Stigmergy GC & gravitons"},"948":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"page","content":"The Memory Bank","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank"},"949":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-0","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-learning--intake--distill--recall","content":"Self-learning — intake → distill → recall"},"950":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-1","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-compacting--heat-decay-eviction-clustering","content":"Self-compacting — heat, decay, eviction, clustering"},"951":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-2","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-distributing--gossip-federation-opt-in","content":"Self-distributing — gossip federation (opt-in)"},"952":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-3","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank#turning-it-on","content":"Turning it on"},"953":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-4","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"Status & known limits"},"954":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-5","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank","content":"kern is a self-learning, self-compacting, optionally self-distributing memory substrate."},"955":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-6","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-learning--intake--distill--recall","content":"One daemon per working directory owns one graph. No automatic session capture; knowledge enters two caller-driven ways:"},"956":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-7","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-learning--intake--distill--recall","content":"MCP `ingest` tool, called directly."},"957":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-8","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-learning--intake--distill--recall","content":"`.txt` transcript dropped into `<cwd>/.kern/intake/` — by your agent, a wrapper, or `kern ingest`; kern ships no writer. Daemon drains each delta: one LLM distillation pass extracts durable facts / decisions / preferences as typed claims. Archived to `intake/done/` only after every claim commits; on LLM outage it stays queued — transient failure never loses knowledge."},"958":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-9","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-learning--intake--distill--recall","content":"Recall: `query` MCP tool against the live graph, provenance on every result. Intake is best-effort — daemon or LLM down, the session proceeds and the delta queues."},"959":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-10","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-compacting--heat-decay-eviction-clustering","content":"Every access deposits **heat**; heat decays with age (half-life based)."},"960":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-11","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-compacting--heat-decay-eviction-clustering","content":"**Stigmergy GC** evicts cold, stale, non-durable thoughts (Facts immune), spilling each to the capped cold tier first."},"961":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-12","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-compacting--heat-decay-eviction-clustering","content":"**Clustering** consolidates similar thoughts into child kerns."},"962":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-13","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-compacting--heat-decay-eviction-clustering","content":"Driven by the maintenance tick (`[tick] interval_secs`, default 60s). `interval_secs = 0`: event-driven only."},"963":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-14","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#self-distributing--gossip-federation-opt-in","content":"LAN gossip between nodes, no coordinator, optional UDP multicast discovery. &#x2A;*Off by default.**"},"964":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-15","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#turning-it-on","content":"`<cwd>/.kern/kern.toml`:"},"965":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-16","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#turning-it-on","content":"Intake and recall no-op without `.kern/` — a single global MCP registration is safe across all projects."},"966":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-17","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#turning-it-on","content":"Seed once: add `graviton`s — named top-level buckets the root routes memories into (unmatched → `generic`). Built-in claim kinds: `preference`, `decision`, `project`, `fact`, `code-fact`, `reference`, `procedural`; register extras with `claim_kind`. See Seed the graph."},"967":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-18","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"Self-learning and self-compaction run today. Self-distribution is wired and enableable, but narrower than the design:"},"968":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-19","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"**Graph CRDT.** Content-addressed, conflict-free merge. Peer ranking signals stripped on the way in — heat, access counts, confidence reset to neutral, so a compromised node cannot pin a poisoned claim hot federation-wide. Heat and confidence are earned by local use only."},"969":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-20","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"**Capped cold tier.** GC spills evictions to a cold table holding the newest 50k entries. Drops past the cap are unrecoverable, counted as `cold_evicted` on `health`. Recall reaches the tier via `kern get <id>` and via `query` filling remaining slots from cold-tier cosine search (marked `cold:true`)."},"970":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-21","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"**Bi-temporal invalidation.** Same-kind near-duplicate that updates or contradicts a stored claim *supersedes* it (stamped `valid_to` / `invalidated_at`, `Supersedes` edge), never deletes. `query` takes `as_of` (point-in-time) and `include_history` (superseded revisions, marked `history:true`). Update-vs-contradiction is a background LLM classification; no LLM → differing near-dup kept as a `Rephrase` edge (fail open)."},"971":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-22","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"**Federation.** Verified end-to-end on one host: two daemons propagate scope and thought bodies bidirectionally. Manually seeding `peers` is the reliable path; multicast discovery only pairs nodes sharing a `network_id`. Still `building` — read Federation and Security before enabling."},"972":{"id":"/howto/memory-bank-23","page_id":"/howto/memory-bank","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/memory-bank#status--known-limits","content":"Near-duplicate ingest is non-destructive: above the similarity threshold, it bumps the existing thought's confidence and records a `Rephrase` edge."},"973":{"id":"/howto/seed","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"page","content":"Seed the graph","breadcrumbs":["Docs","How-to"],"tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed"},"974":{"id":"/howto/seed-0","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Step 1 — Add gravitons"},"975":{"id":"/howto/seed-1","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#step-2--register-claim-kinds-optional","content":"Step 2 — Register claim kinds (optional)"},"976":{"id":"/howto/seed-2","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#step-3--push-the-content-in","content":"Step 3 — Push the content in"},"977":{"id":"/howto/seed-3","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"Direct ingest, per document"},"978":{"id":"/howto/seed-4","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"Bulk, through the intake"},"979":{"id":"/howto/seed-5","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"What happens to your text on the way in"},"980":{"id":"/howto/seed-6","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#step-4--check-it-landed","content":"Step 4 — Check it landed"},"981":{"id":"/howto/seed-7","page_id":"/howto/seed","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/howto/seed#after-seeding","content":"After seeding"},"982":{"id":"/howto/seed-8","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed","content":"Push existing knowledge — design docs, ADRs, README, notes — into a fresh graph. Needs a running daemon (Install & run) and a reachable embedder — nothing is stored if the embedder is down."},"983":{"id":"/howto/seed-9","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Named focus areas: ingest routes each thought to the nearest one, ranking boosts thoughts near one. Seed first — content ingested before any graviton exists lands in `generic` and stays there."},"984":{"id":"/howto/seed-10","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"MCP `graviton` tool, once per focus area:"},"985":{"id":"/howto/seed-11","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"CLI equivalent:"},"986":{"id":"/howto/seed-12","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Rules:"},"987":{"id":"/howto/seed-13","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"**Example statements, one per line** — shaped like the claims you want routed there. Each line embedded separately, mean-pooled into the pull vector; measured to route markedly better than an abstract description or one concatenated blob."},"988":{"id":"/howto/seed-14","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Each line is one embed call, no chunking — keep it under the embedding model's context window."},"989":{"id":"/howto/seed-15","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Optional `mass` (default `1.0`): routing compares `distance / mass`, so `mass = 2.0` claims content from roughly twice as far away."},"990":{"id":"/howto/seed-16","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-1--add-gravitons","content":"Too few: one bucket. Too many: each starved. Dense `generic` clusters promote themselves into new gravitons over time."},"991":{"id":"/howto/seed-17","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-2--register-claim-kinds-optional","content":"Built-ins (`preference`, `decision`, `project`, `fact`, `code-fact`, `reference`, `procedural`) cover most material. Extras via `claim_kind`; registered kinds are offered to the distillation LLM alongside built-ins:"},"992":{"id":"/howto/seed-18","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-2--register-claim-kinds-optional","content":"Per-ingest chunking context: free-text `hint` on the `ingest` call — a prompt hint, not a kind."},"993":{"id":"/howto/seed-19","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"`ingest` MCP tool, text plus optional provenance:"},"994":{"id":"/howto/seed-20","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"`sync: true`: blocks until complete, returns the outcome — use when seeding; the fire-and-forget default gives a batch no way to report failures."},"995":{"id":"/howto/seed-21","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"`source`: provenance shape — `inline` (default), `file`, `session`, `agent`, or any other string (treated as a ticket system id)."},"996":{"id":"/howto/seed-22","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"`object_id`: stable identity — re-ingest with the same `object_id` is a revision, not a new object."},"997":{"id":"/howto/seed-23","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"CLI equivalent:"},"998":{"id":"/howto/seed-24","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#direct-ingest-per-document","content":"`kern ingest` opens the graph directly and can race a running daemon — bulk seed via MCP against the live daemon, or CLI with the daemon stopped, never both. Also deliberate: CLI ingest is `user`-sourced at full confidence → **facts**, immune to eviction; MCP callers are agents, clamped below fact confidence, subject to decay. Material that must survive GC forever wants the CLI path."},"999":{"id":"/howto/seed-25","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"Drop files into `<cwd>/.kern/intake/`; daemon drains (default poll 5s):"},"1000":{"id":"/howto/seed-26","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"dropped file"},"1001":{"id":"/howto/seed-27","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"becomes"},"1002":{"id":"/howto/seed-28","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"needs"},"1003":{"id":"/howto/seed-29","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"`*.txt`"},"1004":{"id":"/howto/seed-30","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"a session transcript, distilled into typed claims"},"1005":{"id":"/howto/seed-31","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"the reason LLM"},"1006":{"id":"/howto/seed-32","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"anything else"},"1007":{"id":"/howto/seed-33","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"a `Document`, stored whole and chunked"},"1008":{"id":"/howto/seed-34","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"the embedder only"},"1009":{"id":"/howto/seed-35","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"not valid UTF-8"},"1010":{"id":"/howto/seed-36","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"quarantined into `.kern/intake/failed/`"},"1011":{"id":"/howto/seed-37","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"—"},"1012":{"id":"/howto/seed-38","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#bulk-through-the-intake","content":"Drained files move to `.kern/intake/done/` once everything ingested; unreachable LLM/embedder leaves them queued for retry. Intake for prose that needs interpreting; direct ingest when the text already is the claim."},"1013":{"id":"/howto/seed-39","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"Direct ingest does no LLM work. Two behaviors shape seed files:"},"1014":{"id":"/howto/seed-40","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"**Paragraph splitting.** Splits on blank lines; whole text also stored as one `Document` alongside the chunks. **One idea per paragraph** — a wall of text becomes one undifferentiated chunk."},"1015":{"id":"/howto/seed-41","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"**Normal acceptance per chunk.** Graph-wide near-duplicate check (cosine ≥ the preset's dedup threshold, `0.98` on the default `relaxed`), then routing to the nearest graviton. Re-running a seed collapses byte-identical content; a reworded version dedupes only above the threshold."},"1016":{"id":"/howto/seed-42","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"Contradiction handling applies: a document may supersede a stored claim, but only on a same-kind near-duplicate with an unambiguous classifier verdict — anything less leaves both standing."},"1017":{"id":"/howto/seed-43","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#what-happens-to-your-text-on-the-way-in","content":"→ Acceptance & routing · Time & contradiction"},"1018":{"id":"/howto/seed-44","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-4--check-it-landed","content":"**Thought count moved** roughly as expected. Zero → embedding failed; see Configure models."},"1019":{"id":"/howto/seed-45","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-4--check-it-landed","content":"**Thoughts distributed across gravitons.** All-in-one: graviton texts too similar, or content seeded before gravitons existed."},"1020":{"id":"/howto/seed-46","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-4--check-it-landed","content":"**No `MISMATCH` on `embed:`.** If present: `kern reembed` before trusting the counts."},"1021":{"id":"/howto/seed-47","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#step-4--check-it-landed","content":"Confirm retrieval (from MCP, the `query` tool exercises the full pipeline):"},"1022":{"id":"/howto/seed-48","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#after-seeding","content":"Nothing further. Sessions populate via the intake; the tick folds seeded content into the same heat, decay, and clustering cycle."},"1023":{"id":"/howto/seed-49","page_id":"/howto/seed","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/howto/seed#after-seeding","content":"→ Intake & recall · Heat, decay & self-compaction"}},"count":1023},"sorting":{"language":"english","sortableProperties":["content","page_id","type","url"],"sortablePropertiesWithTypes":{"content":"string","page_id":"string","type":"string","url":"string"},"sorts":{"content":{"docs":{"1":572,"2":843,"3":486,"4":449,"5":95,"6":661,"7":552,"8":1013,"9":815,"10":57,"11":477,"12":120,"13":765,"14":274,"15":428,"16":336,"17":800,"18":625,"19":1001,"20":702,"21":37,"22":24,"23":703,"24":791,"25":276,"26":337,"27":743,"28":454,"29":632,"30":690,"31":594,"32":261,"33":825,"34":584,"35":968,"36":178,"37":530,"38":151,"39":234,"40":180,"41":710,"42":155,"43":242,"44":146,"45":265,"46":190,"47":296,"48":179,"49":248,"50":566,"51":208,"52":429,"53":416,"54":798,"55":252,"56":417,"57":347,"58":640,"59":876,"60":499,"61":761,"62":374,"63":656,"64":303,"65":709,"66":887,"67":974,"68":688,"69":915,"70":472,"71":851,"72":705,"73":212,"74":394,"75":989,"76":699,"77":879,"78":427,"79":59