:161,"887":207,"888":153,"889":681,"890":844,"891":200,"892":63,"893":78,"894":89,"895":177,"896":194,"897":325,"898":781,"899":1016,"900":216,"901":219,"902":223,"903":764,"904":1020,"905":827,"906":227,"907":229,"908":615,"909":655,"910":500,"911":852,"912":388,"913":1012,"914":698,"915":841,"916":18,"917":9,"918":11,"919":14,"920":6,"921":5,"922":4,"923":15,"924":16,"925":8,"926":3,"927":17,"928":19,"929":7,"930":12,"931":404,"932":597,"933":362,"934":679,"935":13,"936":99,"937":117,"938":96,"939":34,"940":84,"941":542,"942":616,"943":322,"944":360,"945":560,"946":905,"947":860,"948":896,"949":822,"950":820,"951":821,"952":940,"953":850,"954":576,"955":701,"956":614,"957":130,"958":770,"959":460,"960":100,"961":30,"962":437,"963":590,"964":135,"965":561,"966":814,"967":823,"968":51,"969":29,"970":27,"971":47,"972":641,"973":819,"974":855,"975":856,"976":857,"977":422,"978":331,"979":966,"980":858,"981":281,"982":750,"983":639,"984":613,"985":340,"986":802,"987":42,"988":444,"989":715,"990":925,"991":330,"992":729,"993":166,"994":203,"995":197,"996":176,"997":341,"998":168,"999":438,"1000":439,"1001":316,"1002":642,"1003":134,"1004":264,"1005":901,"1006":300,"1007":231,"1008":884,"1009":685,"1010":751,"1011":0,"1012":435,"1013":421,"1014":81,"1015":75,"1016":370,"1017":210,"1018":107,"1019":108,"1020":73,"1021":361,"1022":687,"1023":211},"orderedDocs":[[1011,"—"],[409,"\"Deadline is March\", then \"moved to April\": a vector store holds both — near-identical embeddings, opposite meanings — and returns whichever ranks higher. Deleting the old one loses \"what did we think in January?\", the audit trail, and the evidence it moved at all."],[432,"**`as_of <timestamp>`** — pure world-time filter: the single revision whose validity window covered that instant. Exact over the cold tier too."],[926,"**`claim_kind`** — `add` with a markdown `description`, or `rm`; extends the built-in set distillation may label with."],[922,"**`degrade`** — feedback. Bad result's id as `query_id`: edges along that path lose score."],[921,"**`forget_by_source`** — the host-deletion cascade: remove every thought ingested from one source, all its sections, edges cascaded. Keys on `scheme` + `object_id`. Local Facts are spared unless `force: true`; a remote Fact goes either way."],[920,"**`forget`** — remove a thought, cascade-delete its edges. Facts immune; rewrite history via superseding `ingest` with the same `object_id`."],[929,"**`gc`** — reap empty/orphan kerns live. Returns before/after counts and `data.mdb` size (may not drop — LMDB returns disk only on compaction: next restart or offline `kern compact`)."],[925,"**`graviton`** — focus attractors. `add` with name and seed `text` (example statements, one per line — Seed the graph), optional `mass` (routing divides distance by mass); `list`, `remove`. Unmatched → `generic`."],[917,"**`health`** — counts plus degradation: tick queue and latency, `task_panics` / `task_failures`, `cold_evicted`, `embed_model` / `embed_dim` with `embed_mismatch`. kern fails open — a degraded daemon keeps serving and shows up only here."],[433,"**`include_history`** — normal query, then walks the supersede chain backward from each hit; ancestors flagged `history:true` (recovered from cold if needed). Widens results without loosening filters."],[918,"**`ingest`** — put text in. `object_id` = update semantics for revisions; `hint` folded into the chunking prompt; `conf` weights the claim; `sync: true` blocks until complete."],[930,"**`intake_drain`** — drain `.kern/intake/` now rather than at the next poll: queued `.txt` transcripts distilled, other readable files ingested whole, whatever committed archived into `done/`. No arguments; returns `archived`. `kern intake drain` routes through this, so the CLI and the daemon never drain the same file twice."],[935,"**`kern` on the client's PATH?** GUI clients often don't inherit shell PATH — use an absolute `command`."],[919,"**`link`** — reason edge between two thoughts. Empty `reason`: the LLM writes the justification."],[923,"**`move`** — relocate a thought to another kern (`id`, `to_kern`), edges carried."],[924,"**`promote`** — the release half of the review lifecycle: mark a thought reviewed, moving it from `pending` back to `active` so a `query` asking `exclude_pending` returns it again. Idempotent."],[927,"**`pulse`** — force a clustering pass now. Useful after a bulk seed."],[916,"**`query`** — hybrid vector + lexical retrieval; scored thoughts with edges and path chains, no synthesis. Needs `text` or `id`. Filters: `kind` (`fact` / `document` / `normal`), `source`, `min_conf`; `since` / `before`, `sort` + `ascending`; `as_of` for what was believed at a past instant; `include_history: true` for superseded revisions (flagged `history: true`). Every filter applies to an `id` read too."],[928,"**`setup`** — wiring instructions for the calling agent: seed gravitons, install the capture hook, verify with an ingest/health/query round-trip. Idempotent — reports what is already `[done]`. Once per new project or agent host."],[303,"**A default kern opens no network port** — RPC over an owner-only Unix socket, MCP over stdio, gossip off."],[465,"**A reason edge cannot yet lift its neighbour into the results** — stored and walkable, but the walk's evidence is discarded in scoring; the multi-hop gap is not yet closed. Item 86 in `ROADMAP.md`."],[248,"**Absolute:** an active `Fact` or `Document` is never collected — no heat or age overrides the kind check. A *superseded* fact loses the exemption (excluded from live recall anyway; still spilled, not erased)."],[366,"**Acceptable:** a home or lab LAN you control; a private VPC subnet with the gossip TCP and discovery UDP ports closed to the fleet; a WireGuard-style mesh (the only source of confidentiality and peer authentication today)."],[22,"**Acceptance** — places a claim. Pure vector math + traversal, no model; decides *where* it lives or whether it collapses into an existing thought."],[230,"**Access** — a query returning a thought deposits 1.0 and stamps `accessed_at`. Nothing else deposits. The maintenance pulse walks the tree to schedule work, not to reinforce: it did deposit until it was measured, and because the deposit recurred every tick it settled orders of magnitude above the eviction floor, exempting everything within its reach from collection whether or not anyone used it. Survival is usage, never tree position."],[101,"**Auto-restart on attach** — `kern mcp` compares the daemon's build + config fingerprint against its own; gracefully replaces a stale daemon."],[970,"**Bi-temporal invalidation.** Same-kind near-duplicate that updates or contradicts a stored claim *supersedes* it (stamped `valid_to` / `invalidated_at`, `Supersedes` edge), never deletes. `query` takes `as_of` (point-in-time) and `include_history` (superseded revisions, marked `history:true`). Update-vs-contradiction is a background LLM classification; no LLM → differing near-dup kept as a `Rephrase` edge (fail open)."],[249,"**Bounded:** everything else survives on usage. RAM eviction is lossless; cold eviction is FIFO capped at 50,000 entries. A never-touched non-durable thought behind 50k newer entries is genuinely gone — each drop counted (`cold_evicted` on `health`)."],[969,"**Capped cold tier.** GC spills evictions to a cold table holding the newest 50k entries. Drops past the cap are unrecoverable, counted as `cold_evicted` on `health`. Recall reaches the tier via `kern get <id>` and via `query` filling remaining slots from cold-tier cosine search (marked `cold:true`)."],[961,"**Clustering** consolidates similar thoughts into child kerns."],[272,"**Cold backfill** — fewer than `k` hot results scans the cold tier, flags hits `cold:true`; `as_of` stays exact over backfill."],[244,"**Cold** — age-decayed heat below 0.01."],[190,"**Confidence** — Beta distribution; corroborations and contradictions are observations, so a claim seen five times outranks one seen once."],[939,"**Config aborting the boot?** Invalid `kern.toml` exits **78** with the offending key on stderr — the client sees an immediately dying process. Deleting the file is a valid fix."],[264,"**Dense seeding** — content-vector index + structural (GNN) index, blended 0.4/0.6 (fixed constant, not tuned). Query filters (kind, source, confidence, time window) applied *during* ANN traversal — a filtered top-15 is actually 15."],[118,"**Discovery** — plaintext `kern:<network_id>:<tcp_addr>` broadcast to a UDP multicast group every 10 seconds. Adopted only on matching `network_id` — how unrelated fleets on one LAN stay apart; set a shared `network_id` to pair daemons."],[21,"**Distillation** — transcript → claims. The only LLM call on the path; decides *whether* anything is kept."],[95,"**Entities** (\"thoughts\", \"claims\") — a distilled fact, decision, or preference: typed, evidence-weighted confidence, heat, vector, bi-temporal validity window."],[216,"**Epoch-guarded writes** — a stale in-memory snapshot never overwrites newer disk state."],[383,"**Evaporation** — exponential, lazy, from the age of the last deposit. See Heat & compaction."],[305,"**Everything kern captures transits your LLM endpoints** — localhost Ollama by default. Pointing them at a hosted API is your configuration decision, not a kern default."],[987,"**Example statements, one per line** — shaped like the claims you want routed there. Each line embedded separately, mean-pooled into the pull vector; measured to route markedly better than an abstract description or one concatenated blob."],[269,"**Expansion** — bounded beam search over reason edges from every seed; each surviving path returned as a chain of entities and labelled edges."],[175,"**Explanation** — edges carry a written reason; results return the chain walked."],[429,"**Fails open to coexistence** — hedged, empty, or unparseable = RELATED. A missed contradiction leaves two coexisting claims (recoverable); a false supersede hides a true claim (not)."],[306,"**Federation, when enabled, is unauthenticated and unencrypted** — treat the gossip segment like an unauthenticated internal Redis."],[971,"**Federation.** Verified end-to-end on one host: two daemons propagate scope and thought bodies bidirectionally. Manually seeding `peers` is the reliable path; multicast discovery only pairs nodes sharing a `network_id`. Still `building` — read Federation and Security before enabling."],[94,"**Federation** (off by default) — gossip merges entity bodies with peers."],[271,"**Filter, dedup, MMR** — superseded dropped; delivery floor applies unless nothing clears it (weak results over nothing); same-section chunks collapse to their best; MMR λ 0.75."],[120,"**Gossip** — push flooding with dedup, fanout 3 random peers. Delivery is *probabilistic* — nothing guarantees a message reaches a given peer."],[968,"**Graph CRDT.** Content-addressed, conflict-free merge. Peer ranking signals stripped on the way in — heat, access counts, confidence reset to neutral, so a compromised node cannot pin a poisoned claim hot federation-wide. Heat and confidence are earned by local use only."],[456,"**Gravitons** — named focus attractors bending ingest routing and ranking. One isolated graph per working directory; `degrade` down-weights paths that produced bad answers."],[191,"**Heat + access counts** — drive eviction; see Heat."],[453,"**Heat** on access, exponential decay, stigmergy GC spilling cold thoughts to a capped cold tier. `Fact`s immune. Nobody prunes."],[763,"**Hosted OpenAI-compatible provider:**"],[102,"**Hot reload** (Unix, default on) — daemon watches its own binary; a new build drains, flushes, hands the socket to a successor without dropping connections."],[10,"**How-to** — tasks ·\n**Concepts** — mental model ·\n**Decisions** — why it's built this way"],[266,"**Importance scan** — query-independent third source: anything over a low cosine floor that is a `Fact` or accessed 3+ times. O(N) per query (the clearest scaling gap); down-weighted so popular-but-irrelevant cannot ride to the top."],[389,"**Ingest** — routing picks the child nearest by `cosine_distance / mass`; no match falls to the `generic` catch-all."],[215,"**Int8-quantized vectors** on disk (\\~4× smaller); structural vectors recomputed, not persisted."],[430,"**Kind gates the verdict** — only a same-kind near-duplicate may supersede; a distilled `Claim` never invalidates a user-asserted `Fact`."],[265,"**Lexical seeding** — BM25 over an in-RAM inverted index. Catches the literal tokens embedders smooth away: identifiers, error codes, version strings."],[892,"**LLM endpoint unreachable.** Transient: deltas queue and retry forever. `kern intake` shows them `STUCK` with the reason; confirm with `curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags`. WSL (NAT) with Ollama on the Windows host: `localhost` resolves inside the VM — pin the URL to the host gateway (`ip route show default | awk '{print $3}'`) in `.kern/kern.toml`. Blanking both `[reason].url` and `[embed].url` disables distillation; the daemon logs a warning."],[312,"**LLM endpoints — always, by design.** Every captured text is embedded; distillation and enrichment send memory content as prompt context."],[764,"**Local OpenAI-compatible server** (vLLM, llama.cpp, LM Studio) — `/v1` **required**, else a `localhost` URL is treated as Ollama-native and requests go to `/api/chat`, which your server does not serve:"],[93,"**Maintenance** — tick every 60s: deposit heat, cluster, re-embed, evict, persist. `tick.interval_secs = 0` disables."],[308,"**MCP** — stdio by default; no listener. MCP-over-HTTP is opt-in and never unauthenticated: bearer token from config or a per-graph token file minted `0600` on first use; remote callers without it get a 401."],[304,"**Memory is plaintext on disk** in `.kern/data` — treat it like the source tree it describes."],[270,"**Merge + boosts** — corroboration bonus for entities found by two routes; then score × confidence, an access/recency term, a flat `Fact` bonus, graviton pull (max over gravitons — no double-count)."],[786,"**Merge** — `kern hub merge <src> <dst>` performs an offline CRDT union of\n`src`'s graph into `dst`'s. **Both daemons are stopped first**; `src` is read\nonly and never written. Use it to consolidate a project's graph into another."],[152,"**never imported**"],[148,"**never imported** — content-addressing forbids it"],[1020,"**No `MISMATCH` on `embed:`.** If present: `kern reembed` before trusting the counts."],[176,"**Non-similar relations** — \"deadline is March\" / \"deadline is April\": near-identical vectors, opposite meanings — stored explicitly as a supersede edge. See Time."],[1015,"**Normal acceptance per chunk.** Graph-wide near-duplicate check (cosine ≥ the preset's dedup threshold, `0.98` on the default `relaxed`), then routing to the nearest graviton. Re-running a seed collapses byte-identical content; a reworded version dedupes only above the threshold."],[115,"**Not built:** authentication, encryption, anti-entropy, any guarantee a cold entity eventually reaches every peer."],[243,"**Not durable** — active `Fact`s and `Document`s immune; supersession revokes the immunity."],[893,"**Nothing landing.** Check in order: `.kern/` exists where the daemon pinned; `[intake].enabled` is `true`; something is writing files. Non-UTF-8 → `.kern/intake/failed/`. Endpoint answers but drain never finishes: prose-not-JSON — `kern intake` names it."],[112,"**Off by default** — keep it off unless deliberately experimenting."],[267,"**PageRank** — personalized: teleport to the query's seeds, damping 0.85. What the matching neighbourhood keeps pointing at — a signal cosine cannot produce. Rationale: PageRank for authority."],[1014,"**Paragraph splitting.** Splits on blank lines; whole text also stored as one `Document` alongside the chunks. **One idea per paragraph** — a wall of text becomes one undifferentiated chunk."],[194,"**Provenance** — typed source: file, ticket, session, agent, or inline."],[390,"**Query** — boost proportional to best graviton match × mass (**max**, not sum — overlapping gravitons never double-count). Default weight 0.15; 0 disables; a graviton-free graph pays nothing."],[940,"**Read the logs.** `RUST_LOG=kern=info kern mcp` prints proxy (\"attached to running daemon\") vs standalone (\"auto-spawn failed\"). Spawned daemon output appends to `.kern/data/logs/daemon.log`."],[92,"**Read** — seed candidates, expand over edges, rank, return."],[381,"**Reads deposit** — a returned thought gets an access-count bump, an `accessed_at` stamp, a heat deposit. Deferred to the tick — recall never blocks on a write, never counts as content mutation."],[96,"**Reasons** (edges) — a *justified* link: labeled relation with its own text and vector, not a similarity score."],[459,"**Recall costs no LLM call — you pay at write time.** Ingest distills with an LLM; contradiction checks are more LLM work in the background tick; the read path is a sub-millisecond graph walk. Write-heavy, rarely-recalling workloads get this trade backwards."],[894,"**Recall empty.** `kern health` shows content: check `MISMATCH` beside `embed:` (fix: `kern reembed`). Otherwise widen the query — `min_conf` gates out fresh claims, which start at 0.6 until reinforced."],[428,"**Recall stays LLM-free** — decision made before any query arrives."],[765,"**Remote Ollama** on a non-local host: always driven OpenAI-compatible — point at `http://host:11434/v1` and be explicit."],[783,"**Resolve** a cwd to the daemon serving it (or spawns one and reports the\nsocket path), so `kern mcp` and other clients never have to race the bind\nthemselves."],[307,"**RPC socket** — Unix domain socket, mode `0600`. That permission is the entire access-control story: the socket serves unauthenticated reads and mutations, so only the owning user may reach it."],[268,"**RRF fusion** — by rank, not score: BM25, cosine, and rank mass are not comparable numbers, so no normalization to tune or break."],[5,"**Self-learning memory for AI agents.** One daemon per project, one knowledge\ngraph. Recall = sub-millisecond graph walk. No LLM call at read time, no cloud."],[938,"**Stale socket?** Daemon died hard: remove `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/kern-*.sock`, let `kern mcp` respawn."],[245,"**Stale** — untouched for more than 7 days."],[784,"**Status** — every hub-owned daemon, alive or parked, with its pid and idle\ntime."],[936,"**stdout clean?** JSON-RPC rides stdout; logs go to stderr. A shell profile echoing on startup corrupts the stream."],[960,"**Stigmergy GC** evicts cold, stale, non-durable thoughts (Facts immune), spilling each to the capped cold tier first."],[787,"**Stop** — ends the hub daemon; **nodes stay up**. A node without a hub is\njust a daemon with a socket, still serving its graph."],[211,"**Text and vector never overwritten under an existing id** — a near-duplicate with different phrasing gets a `Rephrase` edge; the tick decides contradiction later."],[155,"**The CRDT does not resolve them — by design.** Different content = different ids; both daemons hold both claims. Resolution is the same local machinery — supersession and validity windows (Time). Federation adds only:"],[731,"**The default.** Keep more, forget slower"],[323,"**The gossip seed — never, unless opted in twice.** Dialed only when both `gossip.enabled` and `gossip.seed` are true."],[382,"**The pulse does not deposit** — it walks from the root at half strength per level to *schedule* work, and lays no pheromone. It used to, and a deposit that recurs every tick never evaporates: everything the walk reached became permanently uncollectible. An idle daemon still maintains itself, on the clustering fan-out, not on manufactured heat."],[1018,"**Thought count moved** roughly as expected. Zero → embedding failed; see Configure models."],[1019,"**Thoughts distributed across gravitons.** All-in-one: graviton texts too similar, or content seeded before gravitons existed."],[174,"**Traversal** — retrieval expands from seeds along edges; a non-matching thought is reachable through one that matches. (Reaching is not yet ranking — caveat in Retrieval.)"],[217,"**Two tiers** — GC spills to the cold tier *before* dropping from memory; a failed spill keeps it hot. Cold tier: capped (50,000 entries), unindexed tail, searched only when the hot graph comes up short. Active `Fact`s and `Document`s never evicted. Past the cap the oldest rows genuinely go — each drop counted by `health`."],[192,"**Two vectors** — content embedding + structural embedding recomputed from the neighbourhood; retrieval blends both."],[367,"**Unacceptable:** any public interface (bind `addr` to a private interface — the default is `0.0.0.0:7400`); coffee-shop or hotel Wi-Fi; a shared office VLAN; any segment carrying hosts you would not allow to read your working memory and inject text into your agent's recall."],[785,"**Unload** an idle hub-owned daemon from memory without stopping the hub."],[193,"**Validity window + status** (`Active`/`Superseded`) — bi-temporal machinery; see Time."],[326,"**Why no authentication yet:** signatures without an identity scheme (key generation, distribution, revocation across multicast-discovered daemons) are worthless, and a half-measure would imply safety the protocol does not provide. Interim rule: **run gossip only on a segment where you trust every host**; get confidentiality from the network layer (WireGuard, VPN). `network_id` is a grouping key broadcast in cleartext, not a credential."],[114,"**Wired but dead:** OR-Set deltas for statement text — content-addressed ids make imported text a forgery; the sender emits empty, the receiver rejects."],[937,"**Working directory right?** Daemon and socket are per-cwd; re-pins to the nearest ancestor with `.kern/` only if one exists above."],[113,"**Works today:** peer heartbeats, multicast discovery, scope announcements, entity-body sync into a quarantined remote namespace, CRDT counter and last-write-wins deltas, single-entity fetch."],[91,"**Write** — claim embedded, deduped, placed."],[12,"/llms.txt — whole system, one page"],[769,"`--embed-url`, `--embed-model`, `--reason-url`, `--reason-model` override config for a single command — test an endpoint before committing it."],[823,"`.kern/data/data.mdb`"],[310,"`.kern/data/data.mdb` is unencrypted. No at-rest encryption planned at this layer: the memory is exactly as sensitive as the code and conversations it was distilled from, which sit unencrypted in the same tree — encrypting one beside the other is theater. If the disk needs protection, full-disk encryption protects both."],[825,"`.kern/data/lock.mdb`"],[833,"`.kern/data/logs/*.log`"],[831,"`.kern/data/mcp-token`"],[827,"`.kern/intake/*`"],[843,"`.kern/intake/` should drain, not accumulate — `kern intake` names anything `STUCK` and why (usually a missing `[reason]` model). Nothing lost; deltas stay queued, and `kern intake drain` forces a pass — through the daemon when one is serving, in-process when none is."],[829,"`.kern/kern.toml`"],[957,"`.txt` transcript dropped into `<cwd>/.kern/intake/` — by your agent, a wrapper, or `kern ingest`; kern ships no writer. Daemon drains each delta: one LLM distillation pass extracts durable facts / decisions / preferences as typed claims. Archived to `intake/done/` only after every claim commits; on LLM outage it stays queued — transient failure never loses knowledge."],[163,"`[gossip]` block (Configure): `enabled = true`, a shared `network_id` across the daemons to pair, prefer an explicit `peers` list over discovery. Then re-read the callout above and confirm the segment qualifies."],[788,"`[hub]` config (`kern.toml`):"],[414,"`[valid_from, valid_to)`"],[1003,"`*.txt`"],[964,"`<cwd>/.kern/kern.toml`:"],[752,"`<project root>/.kern/kern.toml`"],[754,"`<XDG_CONFIG>/kern/kern.toml`"],[137,"`access_count`, `traversal_count`"],[143,"`accessed_at`, `updated_at`"],[517,"`accessed_at`, `updated_at`"],[434,"`as_of` ≠ `valid_at`. `valid_at` checks an explicit expiry date stamped on a thought; `as_of` checks the supersede-maintained validity window. A claim can be unexpired yet superseded, and vice versa."],[795,"`auto_restart`"],[792,"`auto_start`"],[463,"`building`, not shipped; transport unauthenticated and unencrypted. See Federation and Security."],[182,"`Claim`"],[44,"`code-fact`"],[141,"`created_at`"],[515,"`created_at`"],[417,"`created_at` / `invalidated_at`"],[849,"`data.mdb` shrinks only on compaction — next restart auto-compacts, or `kern compact` offline."],[38,"`decision`"],[184,"`Document`"],[888,"`done/` filling while `.kern/intake/` stays near empty — drain keeping pace."],[715,"`embed`"],[42,"`fact`"],[180,"`Fact`"],[462,"`Fact` is CLI-only (requires full confidence; only the user source reaches it). MCP durability levers: `Document`, or keep the thought warm."],[195,"`from` → `to`, with a kind, optional explanatory text, own vector:"],[321,"`granite4:3b`"],[872,"`graviton` tool, `action: \"add\"` per focus area — e.g. *decisions*, *project state*, *preferences*."],[886,"`gravitons` non-empty — `(none)` means seeding never happened; everything piles into `generic`."],[394,"`health` — graviton, kern, entity, reason counts (fastest way to spot unnamed-kern churn), plus `cold_evicted` — the one place retention stops being lossless."],[139,"`heat`"],[317,"`http://localhost:11434`"],[320,"`http://localhost:11434`"],[993,"`ingest` MCP tool, text plus optional provenance:"],[836,"`kern health` or the `health` MCP tool:"],[998,"`kern ingest` opens the graph directly and can race a running daemon — bulk seed via MCP against the live daemon, or CLI with the daemon stopped, never both. Also deliberate: CLI ingest is `user`-sourced at full confidence → **facts**, immune to eviction; MCP callers are agents, clamped below fact confidence, subject to decay. Material that must survive GC forever wants the CLI path."],[794,"`kern mcp` spawn-attaches a detached hub when none answers, the same way it auto-spawns a project daemon. `false` = hub is opt-in via `kern hub`, and the direct-connect fallback still works."],[743,"`kern promote` routes to a running daemon over its local socket. The socket is owner-only (`0600`) and authenticated with the graph's `mcp-token`; any caller holding that token can release a held claim. kern has no finer-grained caller identity — the process boundary is the access model."],[845,"`kern status` answers who is serving and who is writing:"],[866,"`kern` on PATH, local Ollama with both default models:"],[733,"`medium`"],[841,"`MISMATCH` on the `embed:` line: index built with a different model — `kern reembed`."],[766,"`num_ctx` (embed 2048, reason 8192) and `keep_alive` (embed 10m, reason 2m) are compiled-in constants, Ollama-native only. On the `/v1` path kern sends none of them."],[996,"`object_id`: stable identity — re-ingest with the same `object_id` is a revision, not a new object."],[895,"`poll_secs = 0` rejected by the validator (busy-loop)."],[36,"`preference`"],[48,"`procedural`"],[40,"`project`"],[200,"`Provenance`"],[883,"`query` MCP tool: `mode`, `kind`, `source`, time ranges, `min_conf`, `as_of` (point-in-time), `include_history` (supersede chains). Returns scored passages, edges, chains — the agent synthesizes. See Retrieval."],[747,"`query` returns scored passages; the calling agent synthesizes. A config carrying an `[answer]` section refuses to load."],[99,"`query`, `ingest`, `link`, `forget` (Facts are immune), `degrade`, `move`, `health`, `graviton`, `claim_kind`, `pulse`, `gc`, `intake_drain`, `setup`. Transports: stdio default, HTTP/SSE opt-in. See MCP tools."],[186,"`Question` / `Conclusion`"],[206,"`Question` / `Spawn` / `Ratification`"],[318,"`qwen3-embedding:0.6b`"],[716,"`reason`"],[885,"`reasons` well above `thoughts` — claims connecting, not just arriving."],[46,"`reference`"],[730,"`relaxed`"],[739,"`relaxed` when losing a stray fact hurts more than noise; `tight` for high-churn codebases where stale memory misleads."],[204,"`Rephrase`"],[896,"`retention_secs` is the standing per-source policy behind `kern ingest --retention-secs`: \"everything dropped in this queue expires in 30 days\"\n(`2592000`), said once instead of per call. It becomes a `valid_until` on the\nentity — distinct from `done_retention_secs`, which prunes the archived *files*\nin `done/`. The file watcher has the same key for the same reason:"],[740,"`review_policy` keys a curation state on the source scheme — `file`, `ticket`, `session`, `agent`, `inline`. A scheme set to `pending` arrives held; a scheme you do not name arrives `active`, which is every ingest path today."],[198,"`Similarity`"],[995,"`source`: provenance shape — `inline` (default), `file`, `session`, `agent`, or any other string (treated as a ticket system id)."],[149,"`status`"],[521,"`status`"],[891,"`STUCK` carries the last failure and is the whole diagnosis; `wait` means not picked up yet. `kern intake drain` forces one pass — routed to the daemon when one is serving so it never drains twice, in this process when none is — so you can drive the queue with no daemon at all and read the error immediately."],[157,"`superseded_by` converges deterministically (lexically greater id wins — a tiebreak for agreement, not correctness)."],[202,"`Supersedes`"],[994,"`sync: true`: blocks until complete, returns the outcome — use when seeding; the fire-and-forget default gives a batch no way to report failures."],[736,"`tight`"],[793,"`true`"],[796,"`true`"],[887,"`unnamed` small relative to `thoughts` — large share means gravitons don't cover the content."],[51,"`valid_from` kept only when it parses as a real ISO timestamp."],[145,"`valid_until`, reason score"],[1017,"→ Acceptance & routing · Time & contradiction"],[1023,"→ Intake & recall · Heat, decay & self-compaction"],[73,"> **Recall costs no LLM call.** The default query path is a sub-millisecond graph walk — no network hop, no model, no cloud. All expensive thinking happens before the query: LLM at write time, CPU in the background tick."],[342,"0.80 similarity threshold"],[805,"1\\. Install"],[857,"1\\. Opt the project in"],[900,"1\\. Register the server"],[806,"2\\. Opt the project in"],[858,"2\\. Start the daemon"],[901,"2\\. What `kern mcp` does"],[738,"3-day half-life, aggressive dedup (0.90), narrow search (`seed_k` 10, 250 expansions), 12 results"],[859,"3\\. Seed gravitons and claim kinds"],[807,"3\\. Start the daemon"],[902,"3\\. The tools"],[732,"30-day heat half-life, near-identical-only dedup (0.98), broad search (`seed_k` 25, 800 expansions), up to 40 results"],[124,"30s heartbeat; unknown addresses adopted up to a 50-peer ceiling."],[860,"4\\. Drop a session into the intake"],[906,"4\\. Verify"],[861,"5\\. Recall in the next session"],[907,"5\\. Zero tools in the client"],[735,"7-day half-life, 0.95 dedup, `seed_k` 15, 500 expansions, 25 results"],[1007,"a `Document`, stored whole and chunked"],[426,"A `Supersedes` edge links new to old."],[283,"A background tick trains a small per-kern GNN over the real reason edges, writing each thought a second, structural vector — thoughts that never share vocabulary drift together if the graph keeps connecting them. Weighted 0.6 in dense seeding. Needs 128+ thoughts in a kern; the most expensive background cost."],[39,"A choice made, with rationale."],[185,"A chunk of an ingested source document."],[797,"A client attaching to a daemon built from a different binary, or booted against a different config, restarts that daemon before proxying. Without this a long-lived detached daemon serves stale code and stale config indefinitely — the failure that makes every shipped fix look like it did nothing."],[719,"A complete Ollama config"],[725,"A config file only overrides; omitted sections keep their defaults."],[627,"A coordinator"],[234,"A deposit decays first, then adds — touching a stale thought does not resurrect its old magnitude. GC ages the value *before* comparing — no evading eviction on a stale stored number."],[212,"A duplicate (cosine above the preset's dedup threshold — 0.98 on default `relaxed`) is not discarded: it bumps the existing thought's confidence."],[43,"A durable truth about the domain."],[242,"A GC victim only when **all three** hold:"],[80,"A graph, not a vector bag"],[387,"A graviton: name, pull vector, scalar `mass` (default 1.0). Manage with the `graviton` MCP tool (`action=list|add|remove`). Seed text: **example statements, one per line** — each line embedded separately, mean = pull vector. Measured: pooled examples sit markedly closer to held-out same-focus claims than an abstract description. Keep each line under the embedding model's context window."],[798,"A hub-owned daemon idle for `--idle-unload-secs` (default **1800 s** = 30 min) is\nunloaded and re-spawned on next contact; `0` disables. The root daemon is never\nauto-unloaded. Idle time is stamped in the MCP dispatch core and every typed\nRPC method, and the reaper double-checks under the root lock — a node that\ntouched anything between the sweep scheduling and the sweep running stays."],[134,"A leader among sometimes-offline laptops means stalling or failover; a lock puts a round trip on the write path. CRDT joins are commutative, associative, idempotent — duplicate, reordered, weeks-late messages converge: **strong eventual consistency**, no coordination."],[49,"A learned workflow or convention."],[489,"a lone `conf=1.0` write fixes truth"],[782,"A machine-level supervisor that owns detached kern daemons. It is not a server\nof graphs — each daemon still owns its own per-cwd graph and socket — it is the\none process a host runs to spawn, find, unload, and stop them."],[742,"A misspelled scheme refuses to load rather than holding nothing and reading as a working knob. `kern promote` is idempotent — releasing an already-active thought reports it and changes nothing."],[55,"A named kern can refuse — a poor fit lands in a reusable unnamed holding-pen child, descent continues."],[126,"A node's root scope; stored by receivers as a read-only *phantom kern*."],[240,"A panicking task costs that task, not the loop — logged, counted, reported by `health` (`task_panics` / `task_failures`; a climbing failure count means a task gives up every beat). Hourly, not per beat: stigmergy GC and disk consolidation; both refuse to run under an unreadable or skewed clock."],[351,"A peer **cannot**"],[335,"A peer on the segment **can**"],[702,"a peer's usage is not evidence of yours; an injection surface"],[334,"A poisoned message kills its own connection task, not the daemon."],[669,"A power iteration per query, nothing persisted between queries — and nothing *can* be, because the teleport is personalised: a per-graph vector would be the global PageRank rejected above. The walk is confined to the seeds' reach, so it costs what the query touches, not what the graph holds; a query whose seeds reach the whole graph still pays for the whole graph. No incremental updates."],[263,"A query seeds candidates from three sources (dense vectors, BM25, importance scan), fuses them by rank, walks the reason graph, then boosts, filters, diversifies. LLM-free except embedding the query text — no HyDE, no rerank, no synthesis; the caller gets scored thoughts, edges, and path chains, and synthesizes itself."],[32,"A reason model that persistently answers in prose looks like a permanent outage: deltas never lost, never archived, intake retries forever. `.kern/intake/` growing while the graph does not → suspect the model's instruction following."],[498,"A same-kind near-duplicate whose text conflicts goes to an LLM classifier on\nthe background tick; an unambiguous verdict supersedes the old claim outright.\nBeta confidence answers \"how corroborated\"; supersession answers \"which\nrevision is current\". See Time & contradiction."],[664,"a second eigenvector to maintain; bipartite framing fits query/doc graphs, not a reason graph"],[1004,"a session transcript, distilled into typed claims"],[45,"A structural truth about the codebase."],[491,"a tentative guess and a firm assertion each count 1; no principled uncertainty"],[420,"A thought with no temporal information is always considered valid — the conservative default; the alternative would silently hide everything written before the temporal machinery existed."],[477,"A thought's confidence is a Beta distribution — pseudo-counts `conf_alpha`/`conf_beta` updated by weighted observations, ranking multiplied by the posterior mean — not a scalar the latest writer overwrites."],[208,"A transcript in `.kern/intake/` is never stored as memory. One LLM pass distills typed claims — atomic (independently retrievable, supersedable), typed at birth (kind-aware retention), deduplicated against everything known. Empty distillation archives the delta; no output at all (outage) leaves it queued for retry — nothing silently lost. See Acceptance."],[161,"Acceptable: a segment where you trust every host — home or lab LAN, private VPC subnet, WireGuard mesh (also the only confidentiality today). Firewall the gossip TCP and discovery UDP ports; bind `addr` to a private interface, not the default `0.0.0.0:7400`."],[398,"Acceptance — how effective distance places a thought."],[289,"Acceptance — how thoughts get in."],[457,"Acceptance · Stigmergy"],[14,"Acceptance & routing"],[513,"access / traversal counters"],[25,"Action"],[132,"Activation spreading, cross-network questions, the single-entity fetch backing them."],[707,"Active `Fact` and `Document` entities are immune to collection (locally — peers\ncannot pin storage by labelling gossip `kind=Fact`). Supersession revokes the\nimmunity. See Heat & compaction."],[579,"Adjudication runs on the background tick — not at query time, not synchronously at ingest."],[639,"Adopted on paper, not built:"],[981,"After seeding"],[441,"Agent sessions forget — the next one re-asks settled questions, re-proposes rejected approaches. kern is a memory daemon: a self-maintaining knowledge graph per project, served back in under a millisecond with no LLM call at recall time."],[820,"All under `<project>/.kern/`:"],[86,"All-internal, no pluggable backend"],[850,"Alpha: store format changes are not migrated — an old `data.mdb` is rejected; wipe `.kern/data` and reingest."],[189,"Also on a thought:"],[311,"Also under `.kern/data`: the MCP token file (`0600`), and `logs/*.log` — owner-only, append-only, and at `RUST_LOG=debug` they can include graph content. Back up or sync `.kern/` with the same policy as a private repo."],[353,"Alter or delete the text of any entity you hold"],[486,"Alternative"],[526,"Alternative"],[553,"Alternative"],[581,"Alternative"],[625,"Alternative"],[657,"Alternative"],[689,"Alternative"],[47,"An external pointer worth keeping."],[87,"An external store adds a network hop to the one path that must stay sub-ms."],[380,"Ants deposit pheromone; other ants prefer marked paths; pheromone evaporates — the route emerges from the medium. That is stigmergy. The loan ends there: kern's mechanism is exponential decay plus a threshold test. Why this over scheduled cleanup: Stigmergy over gardening."],[552,"Any build or open failure falls back to the resident index — a disk error never breaks the graph."],[1006,"anything else"],[878,"Anything writing a `.txt` delta into `.kern/intake/` feeds kern — client hook, shell wrapper, your own script:"],[325,"Applies only after `[gossip] enabled = true`. Raw TCP plus plaintext UDP discovery — no encryption, no authentication, no signatures. Sniffing the segment reads every shared thought; reaching the port speaks the protocol."],[64,"Architecture"],[470,"Architecture"],[854,"Architecture"],[466,"Architecture implemented, self-maintenance works; hop-dependent recall not delivered yet."],[881,"Archived deltas pruned after seven days."],[199,"Attached at commit to the nearest neighbour — no thought is isolated."],[375,"Auto-promotion out of `generic`"],[777,"Auto-start and auto-rest