n two ingested claims moves only one of 8 pairs by one\nrank. Graph structure currently decides very little of the delivered ranking;\nROADMAP item 86 carries the diagnosis."],[948,"The Memory Bank"],[371,"The metaphor"],[562,"the original target, dissolved before wiring landed — cold tier moved to LMDB with a bounded scan; the real ceiling was the hot resident index"],[726,"The preset owns every heat, dedup, and retrieval-breadth setting. `[heat]`, `[ingest]`, `[retrieval]` sections are not accepted — a config that sets them refuses to load. The one exception is `[ingest] review_policy` below, which is curation rather than tuning. Unknown preset name: refuses to load."],[706,"The pulse used to deposit too, and a recurring deposit of *any* size settles far above the `0.01` gate: everything within its 5-level reach was permanently exempt from collection, used or not. Removed — retention is a consequence of use only (`tests/depth_bias.rs`)."],[1005,"the reason LLM"],[547,"The resident index holds every vector and HNSW layer on the heap; RSS and load time grow with the corpus without bound."],[257,"The retrieval pipeline"],[774,"The retrieval pipeline"],[946,"The retrieval pipeline"],[241,"The structural half of compaction. Per kern, the tick groups sampled thoughts by cosine; a cluster becomes its own child kern when the parent is named, the cluster is not restating the parent's graviton, size ≥ 10, cohesion ≥ 0.60. A cohesive child gets LLM-named — a graviton, a real routing target. Reverse in the same pass: unnamed, empty children fold back into their parent."],[576,"The supersede chain is already a minimal history: nothing erased, both temporal clocks stamped, walkable via `as_of` / `include_history` — append-only revisions without a second storage mechanism."],[221,"The tick"],[372,"The trace"],[438,"The trade"],[302,"The trust model as implemented today: what the daemon exposes locally, what leaves the machine, and what a network peer can and cannot do once federation is enabled — including the parts that protect nothing."],[714,"The two model roles"],[717,"There is no answer role"],[419,"They come apart routinely: learn Friday about Monday's reversal; backfill six months in an afternoon; \"what did the system believe on the 3rd?\" vs \"what was true on the 3rd?\"."],[69,"Thirteen MCP tools"],[201,"Thought → its source document."],[166,"Thoughts"],[213,"Thoughts live in `Kern` containers in a tree. A named kern has a **graviton** — label, centroid vector, mass (default 1.0). Routing descends by `cosine_distance / mass` — a heavier graviton attracts more strongly. The root never holds thoughts; no match falls to a `generic` catch-all. See Acceptance."],[681,"Three knobs total: deposit magnitude, evaporation rate, threshold floor. Everything else emergent."],[448,"Time"],[254,"Time — why a superseded fact loses GC immunity."],[290,"Time — why superseded thoughts never seed; `as_of`."],[401,"Time & contradiction"],[620,"Time is not rounds — kern is a continuous Lamport-ordered stream; anything indexed by round number means nothing here."],[990,"Too few: one bucket. Too many: each starved. Dense `generic` clusters promote themselves into new gravitons over time."],[475,"Trade-off accepted"],[505,"Trade-off accepted"],[544,"Trade-off accepted"],[573,"Trade-off accepted"],[615,"Trade-off accepted"],[649,"Trade-off accepted"],[678,"Trade-off accepted"],[416,"Transaction time"],[424,"Transaction time stamped *now*; world-time window closes when the new claim became true — clocks set independently."],[641,"Trimmed-mean materialisation of federated scalars — written once, never called, deleted."],[665,"TrustRank"],[691,"TTLs"],[864,"Tuning"],[110,"Turning it on"],[952,"Turning it on"],[388,"Two action points:"],[90,"Two caller-driven write entries — MCP `ingest`, or a transcript dropped into `.kern/intake/` — same graph. Four independent loops:"],[403,"Two clocks"],[533,"two concurrent `+1`s must sum to `+2` but LWW keeps one; clock 